title: polly's bourbon balls
directions: Put dates, figs and pecans through the coarsest blade of food grinder.
Mix with diced candied cherries and whiskey.
Shape into marble sized bites, using 2 teaspoons of the mixture.
Roll each marble in coconut.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: granny's christmas punch
directions: Place all ingredients in gallon jug and fill up with water. When ready to serve, pour into punch bowl and add lime sherbet and maraschino cherries.

title: 3 vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables briefly and separately.
Combine all three vegetables and Cheez Whiz while hot.
Pour mushroom soup over all and top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: possum pie
directions: Roll out pastry on 1/4 cup ground pecans before baking or use 1 (9-inch) store bought pie shell.

title: roast or steak on grill
directions: Sprinkle meat with meat tenderizer and pound or pierce meat with fork.
Turn over and do other side.
Place meat on grill; turn about every 5 minutes and baste each time.
Cooking time depends on thickness of meat and how well you like it done.

title: liver and onions
directions: Season liver with salt and pepper.
Roll in flour.
Heat the bacon fat or vegetable oil in skillet.
Fry until golden brown on both sides.
Remove liver from skillet.
Brown onions in the fat. Return liver to skillet and add water gradually.
Stir constantly for 5 minutes.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Fry bacon crisp.
Add onion and all the other ingredients. Bring to boiling point.
Add the potatoes.
Serve warm.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add egg yolks and add soda and milk combined and flour alternately.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes; drain well.
Mix all ingredients until creamy. Put into a 2-quart casserole dish sprayed with Pam.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together cheeses, then add remaining ingredients.
Form into ball and refrigerate.

title: cheese ball
directions: Note:
Have all ingredients at room temperature.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook in iron skillet or heavy boiler.
Cook for 20 minutes slow.
Take off heat and stir in soda.
Spread as thin as possible on well buttered waxed paper.

title: peanut butter chip chocolate cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients adding chips last.
Bake at 350° after chilling dough and shaping into balls, pressed with a fork to flatten, onto a cookie sheet.

title: sonja and sybil's red rice
directions: Wash rice and place in a large pot.
Add all of the remaining ingredients; stir with a large fork until all are well mixed together.
Cook for 1 hour without top on pot.
Stir every 15 minutes until done.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: green pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Stir in mayonnaise to hold together. Mix well.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bring to boil sugar, Karo and 3/4 cup water.
Dissolve the starch in the 1/4 cup water.
Add food coloring.
Add to boiling mixture and stir until clear and thick.
Cool.
Spread a thin layer in cooked pie shell.
Put in fresh whole berries; put rest of glaze over berries.
Top with whipped cream.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Wash broccoli; cut off and discard heavy stems. Slice and set aside 1 cup flowerets.
Chop remaining broccoli which will make about 4 cups. Set aside.
Melt butter in a large pan or Dutch oven.

Saute onion, garlic and celery in butter about 2 minutes. Add chopped broccoli, chicken broth, parsley and white pepper. Cook, covered, about 10 minutes or until broccoli is just tender. Puree in blender with milk until smooth. Return to cooking pan. Stir in lemon juice and whisk in heavy cream. Cook flowerets until crisp-tender, about 3 minutes. Add to soup; taste. Add salt if necessary.
Heat.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix vegetable, onion, beans, celery, mayonnaise and cheese. Place in casserole dish and cover with cracker crumbs.
Melt stick of butter and drizzle over casserole.
Add water chestnuts if desired.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: easy cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage and put in casserole.
Mix flour, sugar, cream, salt and pepper.
Pour over cabbage; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn chowder
directions: In large saucepan, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon, crumble and set aside.
Reserve 3 tablespoons of bacon drippings in saucepan; discard remainder.
Add onion slices; cook until lightly browned.
Add diced potatoes and water.
Cook over medium heat until potatoes are tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Add corn, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour into bowls.
Top each with crumbled bacon and a pat of butter.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix gelatins in hot water.
Add blueberries and crushed pineapple.
Let firm.
Just before serving, mix cream cheese, sour cream, vanilla and sugar and put on top of jello mix.
Top this with chopped nuts.

title: herb vinegar
directions: Place fresh, clean herbs in a clean jar with clamp top lid. Bring 2 cups of vinegar to boil and pour over herbs.
Seal and leave to infuse for at least 2 weeks, shaking jar occasionally. To store: strain vinegar into clean jar or bottle and seal with cork.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberries and sugar; let stand for 1 hour.
Dissolve orange jello in 3 cups boiling water and add lemon juice.
Add nuts and pineapple (do not drain) to cranberries and sugar.
Mix well and chill.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Boil the chicken until tender.
Bone and skin may be removed, if wanted.
Using water, make a biscuit dough (dough must be firm in texture).
While broth is boiling, drop pieces of dough in. Always drop dough where broth is boiling.
Continue this until you use all your dough.
Don't stir until all the dough is wet.
Add the butter, milk, salt and pepper to taste.
Stir, eat and enjoy.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients together in large bowl and mix well. Pour into pie shell.
Bake in oven at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: heavenly pie
directions: Combine cheese, milk and juice; beat until smooth.
Fold in topping.
Stir in pecans
and fruits.
Pour mixture into pie shells.
Refrigerate several hours.
Makes two pies.

title: boiled custard
directions: Put sweet milk on to cook;
Separate eggs and beat separately. Beat whites until you can slice with a knife.
After you have beaten the yolks, add sugar and beat well.
Stir into the scalding milk with egg beater.
When it begins to look a little creamy and thick, add the stiffly beaten whites.
Let boil a few minutes, stirring constantly.
Flavor to suit taste when cool.

title: leek and potato soup
directions: Discard top half of green part of leeks.
Clean under running water.
Chop and cook with the onion in the butter.
Cook 3 minutes, stirring.
Add potatoes and stock; bring to a boil. Simmer for 15 minutes until potatoes are tender.
Add the cream and bring just to a boil.
Season with salt and pepper to taste and serve hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peanut butter fruit drops
directions: In bowl, beat together peanut butter and butter or margarine. Stir in eggs, honey and milk until well blended.
Stir in candied fruits and peel. Stir in flour, baking powder, baking sodas, cinnamon and nutmeg.

Gradually blend into candied fruit mixture. Drop dough by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet. Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Remove to wire rack; cool.
If desired, top each cookie with additional candied fruit.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: grandma's suet pudding
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Add enough sifted flour, about 2 cups, to make mixture stiff.
Pour in tube pan or round pans and steam 3 hours.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion in salted water for 5 minutes; drain. Combine sour cream, soup and carrot.
Fold into squash mixture and add Parmesan cheese.
Mix melted butter with stuffing mix.
Take out 1 cup for topping.
Put in greased 2 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with topping.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: turkey gumbo soup
directions: Heat broth to boiling.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook slowly, approximately 15 minutes.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Beat egg.

Add melted margarine, flour and sugar; beat again. Add milk, lemon juice and vanilla. Add coconut and stir together. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 45 minutes at 350° or until lightly brown and firm on top.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Combine flour, sugar and juice.
Add pineapple chunks and cheese.
Mix well and put in buttered casserole dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers and drizzle melted margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chess pie banks' way
directions: Blend butter, sugar, flour and half of nutmeg.
After blending well, add eggs.
Mix well.
Pour in milk.
Stir in remaining nutmeg.
Stir well.
Warm mixture to lukewarm.
Pour in pie crust. Bake in oven at 300° to 350° until done.
Pie is done when knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: rice and bean enchiladas
directions: Cook garlic in oil until softened.
Stir in beans, tomatoes, rice, 1/2 cup picante, water, bouillon granules, cumin and oregano.
Bring to boil; cover and simmer 1 minute.
Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in pepper, onions and 1 cup of cheese.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Cream oleo and eggs.
Mix sugar with cocoa and add to oleo mixture.
Beat about 2 minutes and add milk, vanilla and nuts. Pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake about 45 minutes (until done in middle) in a 350° oven.
Just as easy to double and make two pies.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 12 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Combine 1 cup sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour margarine over combined ingredients.
Heat fruit with 1/3 cup sugar.
Place on top of batter.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: corn cakes
directions: In a medium bowl, combine the corn, flour, chives and egg. Beat until well-blended.
Heat a large heavy frying pan, preferably cast iron, over medium-high heat.
Add 2 tablespoons of the oil. When oil is hot, gently drop in the batter by heaping tablespoonfuls and cook cakes until the bottoms are golden brown, about 1 minute.
Turn cakes over and brown other side.
Repeat, using all batter and remaining oil if skillet becomes dry.
Makes 4 servings.

title: georgia's gumbo
directions: Heat roux* in large heavy pot or skillet with oil.
Stir in onion, celery, garlic and green pepper.
Add parsley, scallion tops and stock.
Bring to boil over low heat.
Add okra, shrimp, chicken, chicken parts or sausage and simmer for 30 minutes or until shrimp or other meat has cooked through.
Season to taste, adding cayenne pepper or pepper seed according to taste with salt and pepper.
Serve with dry white rice.
Cook over low heat in skillet until very dark brown.

title: applesauce meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into 10 oblong meat balls.
Place in a long baking dish.
Mix 1/2 cup water with 1/2 cup catsup and pour over meatballs.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 400°.
Remove foil and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, add to well beaten eggs.
Then add other ingredients.
Grease 2 - 9-inch pie pans.
Bake at 375 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: patsy's mean green barbecue sauce
directions: Place Dijon mustard in a medium saucepan.
Add salt, cayenne pepper, black pepper, Wright's liquid smoke and sugar.
Stir well. Set aside.

title: chicken in herbs and wine(4 servings)
directions: Combine chicken broth, white wine, pepper, salt, tarragon, carrots, celery and onions in a large, heavy saucepan or skillet. Simmer 10 minutes.
Add chicken and simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until chicken is white through, but still moist.
Remove chicken and vegetables with slotted spoon to heated platter.
Stir Dijon mustard and chopped parsley into remaining broth and reduce liquid as desired.
Ladle sauce over meat and vegetables or serve separately.
Each serving of meat and vegetables contains approximately 225 calories.

title: split pea soup
directions: Soak dried split peas overnight in a 1/2 pot of water. Skim fat and cook for 3 to 4 hours with onion, carrots, celery and ham bone.

title: escalloped oysters
directions: Mix in buttered baking dish.
Use more cream for richer dish. Canned oysters may be used for part of oysters; improves the flavor.
Mixture should be very soupy with milk or cream.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients except bacon.
Put in dish with bacon on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: greek island candy
directions: Toast pecans with 1/2 stick oleo.
Mix together the sugar, milk and syrup.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add pecans. Add 1/2 stick of oleo and vanilla.
Beat until stiff.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Cool, then peel clusters off paper. Store in airtight container.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Place pineapple in 1-quart casserole dish.
Combine cheese, sugar, flour and sprinkle over pineapple.
Mix margarine with cracker crumbs and sprinkle over cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: cheeseburger loaf
directions: Place the whole egg in a mixing bowl; beat slightly.
Add to this the evaporated milk, cracker crumbs, chopped onion, salt, dry mustard, tomato catsup and ground beef.
Blend thoroughly with hands or blending fork.
Spray medium size loaf pan with Pam. Press 1/2 of meat mixture in pan.
Layer the grated cheese atop meat.
Cover with remaining ingredients.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Remove from oven; allow meat to stand in the pan for 10 minutes.
Invert onto platter and serve.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding enough flour to make dough stiff enough to roll out very thin.
Cut and bake in 375° oven until light brown.

title: low cholesterol pound cake
directions: Cream margarine; gradually add the sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy; add egg substitute 1/4 cup at a time and beat well after each addition.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix until just blended after each addition.
Fold in flavorings.
Pour batter into a 10-inch nonstick Bundt pan coated with cooking spray.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix strawberries and 1/2 cup granulated sugar; reserve.
Mix baking mix, 3 tablespoons granulated sugar, 3 tablespoons margarine and milk until soft dough forms.
Spread in an ungreased round pan, 8 x 1 1/2-inch.
Spread with 1 tablespoon margarine; sprinkle with brown sugar and almonds.
Bake until golden brown, 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool 10 minutes. Split layer horizontally.
Place bottom layer on serving plate. Top with half of strawberries and a layer of topping.
Top with another layer and remaining strawberries.
Garnish with topping. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sour cream fruit salad
directions: Mix and let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: grilled oriental chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chicken, to make marinade. Use a glass container for marinade.
Cook chicken in water for about 20 minutes, covered.
Remove from water and place in marinade.
Refrigerate not less than 4 hours.
Broil over charcoal fire until done.

title: frittata al pomodoro e basilico(open-faced italian omelet with tomato, onions and basil)
directions: Place oil and onion in medium skillet over moderate heat until golden.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon. In separate bowl, beat eggs until light, then stir in sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and the nuts.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
May be served on lettuce for salad or on sherbet for dessert.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring 2 sticks of margarine, water and 4 Tbsp. cocoa to a boil. Remove from heat and add flour, sugar, salt, eggs, sour cream and baking soda.
Bake at 350 degrees for 18 - 20 minutes in cookie sheet type pan.
Remove cake from oven and prepare icing.

title: no cholesterol popover
directions: Grease muffin pans.
Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, mix at medium speed, egg whites until frothy.
Beat in milk and margarine until blended.
Add flour and beat until batter is smooth.
Fill muffin cups about 3/4 full.
Bake 50 minutes then make a small slit in top of each popover to let out steam.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
70 calories each.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown meat in a large saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion and green pepper and cook 5 minutes.
Add olives, mushrooms and tomato sauce and mix lightly.
Stir in tomatoes, water, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco into meat mixture.
Add uncooked spaghetti and bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat to low and simmer about 30 minutes.

title: horseradish beef pot roast
directions: Brown pot roast in oil.
Pour off drippings.
Add salt, pepper, tomato juice, horseradish and onion.
Cover tightly and cook slowly for 3 to 3 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Remove roast to platter.
Add water to cooking liquid to make 2 cups. Thicken with flour to make gravy.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken and andouille gumbo
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan over medium-high heat, brown sausage in 2 tablespoons oil, about 7 minutes.
Remove with a slotted spoon; set aside.
Add chicken pieces; cook until golden brown, about 10 minutes, turning occasionally.
Add the water; cover and cook until chicken is tender, about 30 minutes.
Remove the chicken, leaving the liquid in the pan. When the chicken is cool enough to handle, discard the skin and bones and dice the meat into 1/2-inch cubes.

title: chicken tarragon
directions: In large skillet, heat oil and brown chicken; drain.
Add Lipton mix and tarragon, blended with water and wine.
Simmer, covered, 45 minutes or until tender.
Remove chicken to serving platter and keep warm.
Into skillet, stir in flour blended with cream.
Bring to boiling point, then simmer, stirring constantly, until sauce is thickened, about 5 minutes.
Serve sauce over chicken.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cook chicken in pot with enough water to cover and about 1 tablespoon salt.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and let simmer about 1 hour or until tender.
Remove chicken from water; reserve 1/2 cup broth.
Remove skin from chicken and debone.
Cut into bite size pieces and set aside.
Melt oleo; add onion and saute until tender.
Combine onion mixture with 2 soups, broth and green chilies in a bowl.
Stir well.
Add chili powder to taste.
Mix in chicken.
Crush tortilla chips in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour chicken mixture over chips.
Spread cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Heat corn and milk in saucepan; add beaten egg.
Stir in cracker crumbs and salt and pepper.
Place corn mixture in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese cake squares
directions: Cream butter, sugar, flour and nuts.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Save 1 1/2 cups of crumbs for top.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: puerco adobo
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in blender container and puree. Marinate chops in mixture for 8 to 12 hours.
(Can be done up to 24 hours, but will be very hot!)
Heat oil in skillet (or spray with Pam).
Scrape marinade off meat and discard.
Pan-broil chops 3 to 5 minutes per side.
Serve with a vegetable and/or salad and rice.
Serves 4.

title: beef-n-cheese pie
directions: Brown and drain first 3 ingredients.
Stir into beef mixture, next 4 ingredients.
Simmer until hot.
Unroll and separate into triangles.
Line pie pan to form crust.

title: raisin honey bread pudding
directions: Rinse
raisins
and
drain.
Combine
honey
and
bread cubes. Cook
over low heat and stir until bread absorbs honey (2
to 3 minutes).
Blend milk, eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla. Add
with raisins
to bread cubes.
Pour into buttered baking dish. Sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon.
Place dish in pan of hot
water and
bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until knife inserted
in center
comes out clean.
May serve with caramel sauce.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix well in covered jar.
Shake vigorously before pouring over 1 head of shredded cabbage.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: carolyn's chicken casserole
directions: Cook Rice-A-Roni according to directions on box.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish. Top with crumbled Cheddar crackers.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until hot.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients with wooden spoon.
(Do not use electric mixer.)
Add sugar, oil, water and eggs.
Mix with wooden spoon. Add sour cream and chocolate chips.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Chop broccoli in small pieces.
Frozen broccoli may be used. Add broccoli to chicken broth and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer.
Chop onion and celery fine and saute in 1/4 cup butter until soft.
Add to broth.
Do not boil.
Thicken with flour and water.
Cubes of Velveeta may be added during last phase of cooking.

title: easy oven baked potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes and onions in 1/4-inch slices.
Alternate slices, slightly overlapping, in a single layer in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Combine the rest of the ingredients and drizzle over the potato and onion slices.
Cover with foil and bake at 400° for 40 minutes. Can be cooked in microwave.

title: oven veal
directions: Chop vegetables into large pieces and put into large roasting pan.
Add salt and pepper; stir.
Pour tomato juice over mixture. Place frozen veal patties on top.
Place in oven at 350° until veggies are done.
Can cut veggies smaller and the mixture will be like soup.

title: corn chowder
directions: Heat margarine in a large saucepan and cook onion until tender, but not brown.
Add flour.
Cook and stir for 5 minutes over low heat.
Do not brown!
Add bouillon cubes and hot water, stirring with a whisk to blend.
Simmer for 5 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and bring to the boiling point.
Cool slightly and serve!

title: baked apples
directions: Wash apples. Core.
Remove a thin strip of the peel from around the center of apple to prevent the peel from bursting. Pour 1/2-inch water into baking pan; fill the centers of apples with the sugar.
Cover and bake at 375° until done. For a good glaze over apples leave cover off and spoon syrup over apples every 10 minutes.
Test by piercing with a toothpick.
Serve for breakfast with cream.

title: baked potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in their skins until done but not mushy.
Cool and chop into small cubes (skins on).
Heat margarine, milk and Velveeta cheese in saucepan until completely melted.
Fold in potatoes.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 30 to 40 minutes until bubbly.
Spread sour cream over the top and sprinkle with crumbled bacon and chopped chives.

title: pumpkin dump cake
directions: Mix
eggs,
sugar,
pumpkin,
spices and milk together. Pour in greased	9
x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over top. Cut thin slices butter;
scatter over top.	Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: skipper's shrimp creole
directions: Cook onions and celery in oil until tender.
Add celery, tomatoes, tomato sauce, broth, chili powder, salt, sugar, thyme, bay leaves, Worcestershire sauce and hot pepper sauce.
Cook 45 minutes, then add chopped green pepper and shrimp.

title: strawberry angel delight
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 1/4 cups boiling water.
Cool slightly and stir in thawed strawberries, sugar and salt.
Chill in refrigerator.
When mixture begins to thicken, fold in Dream Whip. Cover bottom of 8 x 8-inch shallow glass baking dish with torn pieces of cake.
Over this, pour the jello/Dream Whip mixture. Refrigerate at least 5 hours (12 to 24 hours is better).
Keeps 3 days if tightly covered.

title: sweet-sour chicken macadamia
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken in a medium bowl, making a thin batter.
Marinate chicken in the batter 30 minutes. Heat about 3-inches of oil in a heavy saucepan and fry the chicken until crispy golden.
Drain on paper towel and keep warm while preparing Sauce.

title: birthday igloo
directions: Line an igloo shaped mixing bowl with cling wrap width and length (use 2 long sheets).
Slice pound cake thin; line bowl bottom and sides, making sure to cover every crack.
Fill with softened ice cream, pushing down so no air holes appear.
Place remaining slices of cake on top of ice cream; this will be the bottom of the igloo.
Fold the remaining cling wrap over the top and place in freezer to harden.

title: broccoli stuffed vidalia onions
directions: Peel and halve onions.
Parboil in salted water for 12 minutes.
Remove centers, leaving 3/4-inch edges.
Place onion cups in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chop center portions to equal 1 cup.
Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.

title: confetti ice cream punch
directions: Mix fruit punch with water and chill.
If an ice ring is desired, freeze a portion of this base mixture in a ring jello mold until slushy, 1 to 2 hours.
Remove from freezer and place strawberries in the ring at even intervals.
Return to freezer until serving time.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Stir together peanuts, Karo, sugar and salt in a 1 1/2-quart Pyrex measuring bowl (with handle).
Microwave on High for 4 minutes, stir and turn, cook 4 more minutes.
Then add oleo and vanilla, stir and cook 2 minutes.
Add the soda, stir fast.
Pour on ungreased cookie sheet.
Break when cool.

title: mother's cornbread salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir well.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: peanut butter delight
directions: Cook sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa for 2 minutes or bring to boil.
Remove from heat; add oatmeal, vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat until well blended.
Spoon on wax paper, using #40 scoop.
Makes 18 servings (54 cookies).

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese in a bowl with Cool Whip, then add your dry jello and mix good (any flavor).
Then add your drained fruit and refrigerate for 6 hours.
Could be used as an appetizer or dessert.
Never use pineapple fruit.

title: baked beans for 100
directions: Rinse beans and soak overnight in cold water.
Next morning, using same water as soaked in, add 1 teaspoon soda and cook until soft. Drain.
Put in large roaster.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Bake, covered, for 2 to 3 hours in a 325° oven.

title: roasted asparagus
directions: Wash and trim asparagus. Drizzle with olive oil and salt, pepper, and Herbs of Provence. Roast in a 425° oven for about 10-15 minutes, or until desired tenderness. If desired, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese when done. Serve 4.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine corn syrup, sugar and margarine.
Bring mixture to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and cool completely.
When mixture has cooled, add vanilla and beaten eggs, mixing well.
Place pecans in unbaked pie shell.
Carefully pour syrup over the pecans.
Bake 1 hour or until center is set.
If crust starts to get too brown, make a ring of aluminum foil and cover crust.

title: pork chops puget sound(old favorite of bruce reeves family)
directions: Layer meat with
2 sliced onions. Make sauce from other ingredients.
Pour sauce over chops.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: frontier sauce
directions: Stir flour into melted butter.
Add seasonings and Tabasco, then add tomato juice and mushroom liquor gradually and cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly, until smooth and thick.
Add cream and blend.
Serve on macaroni or spaghetti.
Yield:
1 1/4 cups sauce.

title: cranberry salad ring
directions: Dissolve
gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water and chill until consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Combine next 6 ingredients.
Mix
well.
Fold
fruit
mixture into gelatin mixture.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Toss together all ingredients except the cheese and top with cheese.
Bake
in a large greased casserole dish at 350° until boils good and cheese melts.

title: herb cheese wedges
directions: Combine Bisquick, onion, sugar, and herbs.
Mix the egg, milk, and butter together: beat slightly.
Add to dry ingredients. Beat until blended.
turn out into a well greased round 8 inch cake pan.
Sprinkle the cheese on top.
Bake at 400 degrees until crusty and brown, about 25 minutes.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine flour, 1 cup sugar and the milk, blending well.
Spoon evenly over butter, but do not stir.
Combine peaches with remaining cup of sugar in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Ladle over batter; do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about 10 servings.

title: date-nut cookies
directions: Cream margarine with brown sugar.
Add eggs, salt and vanilla. Put soda in boiling water.
Add to the mixture.
Add flour, dates and walnuts.
Drop from spoon.
Bake at 375° for about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Combine pudding mix, cake mix and cooking oil.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend 7-Up into batter.
Pour into three 9-inch layer cake pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from pans and let cool.

title: garden salad
directions: Drain vegetables well.
Mix sugar, vinegar, oil and pepper together, heat to a boil (make sure sugar is dissolved).
Cool. Pour over remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: gazpacho
directions: Plunge tomatoes into boiling water for 30 seconds to loosen skins, then dip into cold water.
Remove skins, core and chop tomatoes.
In a large bowl, combine tomatoes, tomato juice, chopped, seeded cucumber, finely diced onion and green pepper, pressed garlic, oil, vinegar, wine and Tabasco.
Stir.
Cover and chill 1 hour before serving.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions together.
Cover with boiling water and let stand 5 minutes.
Drain.
Add vinegar, sugar and salt; boil for 5 minutes.
Pack in hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Sift flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Combine egg, milk and oil.
Pour into flour mixture and stir enough to moisten flour.
Fold in drained blueberries.
Fill muffin cups about 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.
Makes about 12 muffins.

title: banana nut salad
directions: Place layer of sliced bananas in dish and cover with layer of sauce; sprinkle with Grape-Nuts cereal.
Continue with layers until you have completed three.
Be sure the top is covered completely with Grape-Nuts.
Chill 1 hour before serving.
Use at least 3 medium bananas.

title: diet chocolate peanut butter dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Make crust with the graham crackers and margarine.
Press into oblong pan.
Bake for 8 minutes.
Cool crust.
Beat the ice cream and softened peanut butter; spread on cooled crust.
Freeze.

title: picante sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pot.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 25 to 30 minutes.
Put in hot sterilized jars and seal.
Process in hot water bath for 35 minutes.
Makes about 16 pints.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, onion, bell pepper and rice well; set aside.
Rinse leaves and place in boiler pan; cover with cold water, bring to a boil and cook approximately 2 or 3 minutes. Drain and cool with cold water.
In each leaf, place 1 to 2 tablespoons of mixture in the center.
Fold outer edges of leaves to center, then roll end to end, forming a cylinder.
Place in baking dish.
Pour one can of stewed tomatoes over rolls and bake 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: corn and bean vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all vegetables with soup and sour cream.
Place in flat, buttered casserole dish (11 x 8 1/2-inch).
Melt butter and mix well with crushed crackers; sprinkle over casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: potato-tot casserole
directions: Place in skillet and saute for a few minutes.
Place in a casserole dish and add cream of mushroom soup.
Cover with shredded cheese.
Place potato tots in rows on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: aunt laura's white cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco; add flour, baking powder, salt, flavoring and milk alternately.
When well mixed, fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into 2 lined round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.
Cool before icing.

title: mom's upside-down cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add egg, vanilla and milk.
Add dry ingredients.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine and add pineapple liquid and brown sugar.
Arrange pineapple slices.
Add batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: orange whip
directions: Blend milk, orange juice, sugar and vanilla in blender.
Add ice cubes; mix on high until cubes are crushed.
Yield: 6 glasses. Good at breakfast.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix well and bake 10 to 15 minutes.

title: scott's beef brisket
directions: Combine the dry seasonings and set aside.
Place brisket in a shallow dish or large resealable plastic bag.
Combine cola and Worcestershire sauce; pour over meat.
Cover.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: hot mexican sauce
directions: Using blender, process onion, peppers and garlic together until finely chopped.
Mix in cilantro, tomatoes and cumin. Mixture should be liquid, but smooth and thick.
Season with salt. Serve with any dish.

title: jello punch
directions: Boil together water and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Mix in Jell-O.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice.
Beat eggs and sugar.
Add melted butter, vanilla, milk and raisins.
When rice is done, add all ingredients.
Cook on low heat for 10 to 15 minutes.
Place in bowl; chill.
Add cinnamon on top.

title: italian meat sauce(for spaghetti)
directions: Brown ground round.
Add next nine ingredients and cook 1 hour.
Cook angel hair spaghetti and drain.
Put spaghetti on plates.
Add sauce and sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
After cooking and draining spaghetti, pat about 4 tablespoons oleo in pan and mix into spaghetti.
Serve with French bread, toasted.

title: cabbage and hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Stir in rice.
Put chopped cabbage in baking dish; add hamburger.
Cover with tomato soup and water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken salad casserole
directions: Combine ingredients in 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with 2 cups crushed potato chips.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes, then sprinkle with 1/2 to 1 cup Cheddar cheese (grated) and bake until it melts.

title: homemade fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in pot; turn burner on and add milk, stirring constantly.
Bring to boil; add butter and continue stirring.
Test small amount in cup to see if it gets creamy.
If so, turn off and stir in vanilla beating with spoon until it thickens.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan; cool and cut in pieces.
Enjoy.

title: liver and onions
directions: Saute onions in butter with sage.
Cut calf liver into thin strips.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Coat liver with mixture. Add to onions.
Cook over high heat for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Put liver on warm serving platter.
To pan, add minced parsley, beef stock and dry wine.
Cook 1 minute, stirring in all the brown glaze from bottom of pan.
Pour over the liver and onions.
Serve immediately.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Place all ingredients together in covered baking dish.
Stir mix well.
Bake 4 to 5 hours at 250°.
Serve over rice or noodles. 4 - 6 servings.

title: radish, chives canapes
directions: Bring cheese to room temperature.
Combine butter and cream with fork.
Add chopped radishes, chives or scallions and salt; mix.
Spread 1/4-inch of mixture on bread.
Makes 2 dozen small sandwiches.

title: red beans and rice with cocktail smokies
directions: Cook red beans and rice per package directions.
Poke holes in sausage with fork.
Add sausage halfway through cooking time of red beans and rice.
Finish cooking.

title: gourmet chicken
directions: Place 1 slice of dried beef in center of breast.
Wrap a slice of bacon around rolled up chicken breast.
Place chicken breasts in baking pan and pour over mushroom soup and sour cream mixed together.
Bake, covered, for 2 1/2 hours.
Sprinkle with slivered almonds and bake 1/2 hour, uncovered.

title: karen's broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed and drain.
Mix the eggs, Chederalla cheese, soup and broccoli together and pour in a large casserole dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers and butter that has been cut into small pieces.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Let stand for 15 minutes before eating.

title: poor boy steaks
directions: Mix all ingredients except bacon.
Form into 3 or 4 balls and flatten slightly.
Wrap in bacon strips (secure with toothpick). Grill.

title: baked beans
directions: Add 2 tablespoons ketchup and 2 tablespoons brown sugar for each can of pork and beans.
Lay a few strips of bacon over the top.
Bake, uncovered, in a 325° oven for about 1 hour.

title: sugar-free strawberry pie
directions: Combine ingredients in pan and cook until boiling. Cook until mixture begins to thicken. It will still be thin. Let cool until lukewarm. Slice fresh strawberries (as many as you want) into a cooked pie shell and pour mixture over berries. Chill in refrigerator until jelled. Top with Cool Whip just before serving. Low-fat.

title: tabouleh(middle east)
directions: Pour 4 cups boiling water over bulgur wheat; let stand 2 hours.
Drain well.
Mix with other ingredients.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Serve over lettuce or in pocket pita bread.

title: struedel
directions: Mix flour, salt , sugar and lard; mix well.
Add yeast, egg and milk.
Let stand 1 hour (can be stored in refrigerator).
Roll into square.
Add fruit of choice, such as canned cherries, apple, etc. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Make powdered sugar icing and drizzle on top.
Makes 2 to 3 crusts.

title: cheese ring
directions: Peel cucumbers; core if seeds are large.
Soak cucumbers overnight in lime water.
Lime water = 2 cups lime to 1 gallon water.
Rinse and soak 3 more hours.

title: cherry salad
directions: Combine water, sugar and cherries; boil gently for five minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in Jell-O.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Stir in Coke last.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Stir-fry all ingredients in olive oil in a Dutch oven except tomatoes.
Once chicken is almost cooked add tomatoes and simmer until chicken is cooked through.
Cook the linguine and serve over the linguine.

title: beefy mexican soup
directions: Cook and stir ground beef, onion and green pepper in Dutch oven until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in sauce mix, water, chili powder, garlic, salt and tomatoes.
Break up tomatoes with fork; heat.

title: lemon sauce
directions: In a small saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add 1 cup water, stirring until smooth.
Bring to a boil, while stirring. Lower heat and stir until clear.
Add lemon juice and peel.
Mix thoroughly.
Serve warm over gingerbread, angel food cake or the like.

title: potatoes d'grill
directions: Wash and quarter potatoes.
Place in pie pan or grill-proof dish.
Slice onion and green pepper.
Put over potatoes and dot with butter.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with foil.
Cook on grill 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Remove foil last 15 minutes for browning.
Adjust cooking time for your own grill and quantity cooked.

title: peanut butter clusters
directions: Melt chocolate; stir in peanut butter, then other ingredients. Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: sweet potato muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease muffin tins and fill 2/3 full. Bake at 350° for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients except bacon; pour into shallow baking dish.
Lay bacon strips on top.
Bake in 325 to 350 degree oven for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Mix well, roll out portion at a time, 1/8 inch thick.
Use well floured surface.
Cut out with cookie cutter and bake until brown. (Quantity approximately 200.)

title: jambalaya
directions: Combine all and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Should be done when chicken is cooked, rice is tender and all liquid has been absorbed.

title: german-style noodles and sausage
directions: Brown sausage and onion; drain.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Alternate layers of noodles, sauerkraut and sausage in casserole.
Season to taste.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Add water if needed.
Yields 6 servings.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Slice mushrooms.
Steam broccoli and cauliflower together in a pan.
Drain and set aside.
Slice tomato and set aside.
Grate cheese and set aside.
Dice green onions and set aside.
Place flour tortilla on ungreased pan.
Layer veggies on tortilla: broccoli, cauliflower, mushrooms, onions and tomato.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until the cheese is melted.
Ready to eat!!

title: summer cooler
directions: Blend until smooth.
Freeze.
To serve, put 4 tablespoons in glass.
Add lemon-lime soda or ginger ale.

title: peaches and cream cheesecake
directions: Combine dry ingredients, butter, egg and milk in large bowl and mix for 2 minutes at medium speed. Pour into a well-greased deep-dish or 10-inch pie pan. Place the sliced peaches on top of batter. Beat cream cheese, sugar and reserved juice for 2 minutes on medium speed. Spoon to within 1-inch of the edge of the batter. Combine sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over cream cheese filling. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, until crust is golden brown. Store in refrigerator.

title: st. matthew bean soup
directions: Wash 1 to 1 1/2 cups of bean mix.
Put in large kettle; cover with water.
Soak overnight.
In the morning, drain and add 2 quarts of water and meat of your choice (ham or chopped smoked sausage).
Simmer for about 3 hours, then add onion, red pepper or chili powder (less, if desired), tomatoes, garlic, wine or vinegar and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 1 or 2 hours more.
Enjoy!

title: braised green beans
directions: Pour the oil into the bottom of a heavy saucepan and add the beans, onions, parsley, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer slowly for 20 to 30 minutes or until beans are tender. Serves 6.

title: fresh blueberry pie
directions: Crush 1 1/2 cups of blueberries.
Add sugar, salt, water and cornstarch in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until bubbly and thick.
Add lemon juice and cool.
Add remaining fresh berries and stir to coat.
Fill pie shell.
Top with whipped cream.
Serve chilled.

title: janine's special punch
directions: Combine all ingredients. Chill. Serves 25 people.

title: squash vermicelli
directions: Cook vermicelli in boiling, salted water according to package directions.
Meanwhile, shred zucchini and slice scallions; add to spaghetti water, in the last minute, just until heated through. Drain well.
Return well drained pasta-zucchini mixture to pot. Stir in remaining ingredients and heat gently over lowest heat. Toss together lightly and serve when heated through.
Makes 8 servings.

title: gingerbread
directions: Combine egg, sugar, molasses, butter and water.
Mix well. In a large bowl, stir together flour, baking soda, ginger and salt.
Add molasses mixture.
Beat until well mixed.
Pour into a greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: fruit and nut balls(health food)
directions: Combine fruits, nuts, lemon juice and rind.
Blend well and roll into small balls.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Makes about 36 balls.

title: sweet potato casserole #1
directions: Mix together sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs and vanilla and pour into a buttered pan. Combine brown sugar, flour, margarine and pecans and mix to a crumble. Sprinkle crumbs over top of the potato casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dip for chips
directions: Brown and drain grease off beef and sausage.
Add remaining ingredients; cook over low heat for about 20 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream the margarine or butter and sugar with cream cheese until light and fluffy. Add salt and vanilla. Beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in flour gradually.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: grandma musshorn's raisin squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients as for pie crust.
Add enough water to moisten.
Set aside.

title: creamy vegetable dip
directions: Drain spinach, reserving 2 tablespoons of liquid.
Combine liquid, sour cream, soup mix and mayonnaise.
Stir in spinach and chestnuts.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Serve with crackers, bread or vegetables.

title: meat balls
directions: Make meat balls; drain grease.
Cook about 1 hour with chili sauce and jelly.
Chill and skim off grease.
These can be put in a crock-pot until ready to serve.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix together pretzels, sugar and oleo.
Spread in 8 x 12-inch dish and bake 8 minutes at 400°.
Cool.
Mix together cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar.
Spread over crust.
Dissolve jello in hot water; stir in strawberries and let stand 20 minutes.
Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: avocado dip
directions: Mash avocados to a pulp.
Add other ingredients.
Salt to taste.
Serve with chips.

title: angel puff drink
directions: Pour all ingredients in blender.
Add a few drops of food coloring, red or green.
Do not overbeat!
Put one shot in a barrel glass.
Slowly add chilled cream soda (diet or regular). One ice cube may be added if soda isn't cold.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Combine vegetables.
Combine other ingredients and heat to dissolve sugar.
Pour over veggies.
Chill overnight.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until just done.
Put 1/4 cup butter (oleo) in casserole and melt.
Mix potatoes, cheese, sour cream, onions and green peppers and put in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Mix together oleo and crumbs and put over potatoes and bake 15 minutes more.

title: pasta with shrimp, broccoli
directions: Saute garlic in oil until golden.
Saute shrimp in oil until done, then separate.
Add broth, then boil down 15 minutes.
Boil water.
Add pasta.
Five minutes before pasta is done, add broccoli.
Drain pasta.
Put in pasta dish.
Add shrimp, oil, garlic and broth.
Mix together.
Sprinkle pepper and cheese. Enjoy.
Preparation Time:
30 minutes.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in buttered pie pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
(Can be frozen.)

title: fudge brownies
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs; beat until thoroughly mixed.
Blend in cocoa and flour.
Turn batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Ice with chocolate icing while still hot.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: yellow squash puffs
directions: Cook squash and onion covered in boiling water; drain.
Mash enough squash to measure 1 cup.
Combine 1 cup squash and egg; stir well.
Combine flour, cornmeal, baking powder and salt.
Stir well. Drop squash mixture by level tablespoon into hot oil.
Cook until golden brown, turning once.
Drain on paper towel.

title: pickled okra
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pack raw okra in jars.
Add remaining ingredients to each jar.
Pour hot vinegar solution over okra; seal jar.
Let stand a week or more. Chill before serving.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Whip the lemonade, Cool Whip and milk and pour into pie crust. Chill in refrigerator.

title: baked chicken breasts bileckyj
directions: In saucepan, heat butter with soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce over moderate heat until melted.
Add onion, parsley and spices.
Simmer, stirring, for 5 minutes.
Arrange chicken breasts in a baking dish, spoon mixture over them and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: impossible crabmeat pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in greased 10-inch pie plate. Combine milk and remaining ingredients in blender container or with a mixer.
Process until smooth.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Let stand for 5 minutes before cutting.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Heat to boiling; add vegetables. Bring to a boil again, but do not let boil.
Pack jars and seal.

title: roast beef sandwich grill
directions: Stir together the beef, mayonnaise, pickle relish, salt and pepper.
Place about 1/3 cup mixture on each slice of toast.
Top each with a slice of cheese.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake in 425° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until the cheese is melted and golden brown.

title: elegant eggplant casserole
directions: Saute onions, garlic, peppers and celery in the oleo until soft.
In the meantime, boil eggplant in small amount of water for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Combine sauteed vegetables, eggplant, tomatoes, eggs, cheese, salt, pepper, Tabasco, Worcestershire sauce and crumbs.
Place in greased casserole dish in a 350° preheated oven for 30 minutes.
Serve at once.

title: diana hege's pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add extracts and blend well.
Add eggs, one at a time, and continue beating after each addition.
Sift together dry ingredients and add alternately to creamed mixture with milk. Pour into a greased and floured good size tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until done.

title: aunt eva's party cake
directions: Make custard of the following:
egg yolks, sugar, lemon juice and rind.
Cook in double boiler until it thickens.

title: carrot raisin salad
directions: Fold all ingredients together and chill well before serving. Serves 6 to 8.

title: eggplant, squash or broccoli casserole
directions: Stew vegetable with onion.
Drain and add sour cream, soup and 1/2 cup stuffing.
Melt oleo in baking dish and add remaining stuffing to line bottom of dish.
Pour mix over this and bake about 30 minutes to 1 hour until done.
Add crushed crackers on top and put back in oven to brown slightly.

title: peanut butter cookie dessert
directions: Press purchased or homemade cookie dough on a pizza pan.
Bake at 350° until done.
When cool, spread cream cheese, sugar, vanilla mixture over the top.
Layer sliced apples over this and top with caramel topping drizzled lightly over the apples.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill for 1 hour before serving.
May be served with Cool Whip on top.

title: mother murphey's bill taft cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan or loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until done.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cover bottom of pie shell approximately 1/2-inch with chopped pecans.
Beat eggs with fork until still foamy (not dry).
Add Karo, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well by hand.
Do not use mixer. Pour over pecans and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until center is slightly firm to touch.
Do not overbake.

title: american made
directions: Stir 2 1/2 cups boiling water into red jello.
Dissolve completely.
Slowly pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Repeat with blue jello in another pan.
Refrigerate 3 hours.
Cut into cubes.

title: garlic butter
directions: Blend softened butter or margarine and garlic powder with fork or hand mixer until fluffy.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place bread in oiled pan.
Brown sausage; drain and place on bread.
Add cheese.
Mix eggs, mustard and 2 1/2 cups evaporated milk and pour over cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Add soup and remaining evaporated milk.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in preheated oven at 300°.

title: shrimp pilaf - rice cooker style
directions: Saute chopped onion in butter.
Mix the other ingredients with onion and butter.
Cook in rice cooker until the cooker cuts off on its own.

title: homemade chili
directions: Cook all ingredients, except for beans, for 45 minutes. Add chili beans and stir often, cooking for 20 minutes more.

title: grape-nuts pudding
directions: Stir all ingredients into small microwave-safe dish.
Cover with Saran Wrap; vent.
Microwave on Low (3) for 7 minutes; stir. Microwave for 5 to 7 minutes longer.
This is a low calorie pudding.

title: corn and beans from the oven
directions: Spread drained beans and corn in a casserole dish.
In a saucepan, mix soup, cheese, sour cream and onion.
Heat until cheese is partially melted.
Pour cheese mixture over corn and beans.
Melt margarine in another saucepan and add cracker crumbs and almonds to melted margarine.
Spread crumb mixture on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars together.
Add peanut butter, egg, and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients and mix well. Roll into ball and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press down with fork tines dipped into flour or sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8-10 minutes until the cookies start to brown.
Remove from oven and let cool a few minutes before removing from pan.
They are very fragile and will crumble if they don't cool for 5-10 minutes before removing them.
Yields: 4 dozen.

title: tomato aspic mold
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in mold.
Refrigerate overnight. This makes flavor better.

title: marinade vegetables
directions: Marinate vegetables.
Heat sugar, vinegar and oil.
Heat and pour over vegetables (not boiling).
Salt and pepper to taste. Let set overnight in refrigerator before eating.

title: almost fat-free cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Spray skillet with Pam (or substitute). Heat skillet. Combine all ingredients. Pour into skillet. Bake 30 minutes. (The only fat is in the meal and Pam spray.)

title: white sweepstakes frosting
directions: Mix at high speed until creamy.
Add mixtures together and whip at high speed until light and fluffy.
Can be refrigerated to keep.

title: potatoes marcroft
directions: Cook potatoes, cool, peel, grate then set aside.
Mix the next five ingredients.
Add mixture to potatoes and mix well. Pour into lightly buttered 13 x 9 inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: five cup fruit salad("a favorite from the '76 cookbook.")
directions: Combine all five ingredients and chill before serving.

title: stuffed bread
directions: Hollow out bread and crumble in a bowl.
Mix in water, egg, mustard, salt, pepper, onion and cooked meat. Stuff into bread. Put ends back on bread with toothpick or skewers.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes. Cut in slices.
Pour tomato sauce over and serve.

title: indian pudding
directions: Heat milk, add corn meal, add molasses and cook on
low for 10 - 15 minutes.
Add cinnamon, ginger and salt.
Pour into casserole dish, baking at 300 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms; remove stems and mince them.
Saute mushroom caps in butter until lightly brown.
Remove from heat, then saute minced onion, green pepper, mushroom stems and celery in butter. Add seasonings.
Fill each mushroom cap with mixture.
Sprinkle each with bread crumbs.
Drizzle melted butter on top.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Top each one with a piece of cheese.
Return to oven and bake until cheese is melted.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix beaten egg yolks, brown sugar, salt, flour, milk and butter in double boiler.
Cook over boiling water until thick. Add vanilla. Pour into 9-inch baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites with white sugar and put on top of pie filling.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until egg whites are golden brown.
This tastes like old fashion pie.

title: country stir-fry
directions: Place oil in hot saucepan.
Add onion, pepper and squash. Saute for 2 minutes, stirring lightly.
Add chicken, hominy or corn and water.
Cover with lid; steam an additional 2 minutes. Add soy sauce; stir lightly.
Serve.

title: sage bread
directions: Scald milk with sugar, salt, onion and margarine in pan.
Cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast into water in a large bowl.
Stir until dissolved, then stir in cooled milk mixture.
Stir in flour and sage until well blended.
Beat vigorously, scraping down side of bowl, about 100 strokes.
(Dough will be sticky.)
Cover with clean towel; let rise in warm place for 1 hour or until doubled. Stir dough down; spoon into greased 10-cup tube pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Remove from pan and cool.

title: rich chocolate pecan cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking soda and salt. Mix butter and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.
Add flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Pour melted butter over chopped pecans. Add vanilla, Eagle Brand milk and sugar.
Mix well. Roll into small balls about the size of a quarter.
(Easier to work if mixture is chilled thoroughly before handling.)
Melt chocolate pieces and paraffin in a double boiler. Dip candy in chocolate mixture with toothpick. Place candy on wax paper to cool.
Yields 80 pieces.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together except blueberries and mix at medium speed until smooth. Gently fold in the blueberries.
Grease muffin tins, even the top, and fill with batter.
Sprinkle the tops with granulated sugar.
Bake at 450° for 12 minutes and then turn oven down to 350° for an additional 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12 large muffins.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients by hand and press into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Pour remaining ingredients over cake mix.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Cut squares while hot.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: freezer ice cream (uncooked)
directions: Beat eggs until light; beat in sugar and salt.	Stir in evaporated	milk,
homogenized
milk
and
vanilla.
Pour into gallon-size
ice
cream
freezer
canister.
Pack freezer with crushed ice
and
part ice cream salt.
Turn hand freezer until hard	or
use electric freezer.
Recipe may be varied by adding
crushed fruit before freezing or toppings may be used. If I
use
sweetened
fruit, I just use 2 cups of sugar and do not use the vanilla.

title: gooey butter bars
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs and butter. Spread on cookie sheet. Beat cream cheese, eggs and powdered sugar (add tablespoon lemon juice if desired). Pour over cake mix batter. Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar and nuts (if desired) over top before baking. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes until edges are golden brown. Cool and cut into bars.

title: perky bologna spread
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve on a pretty platter.

title: squash casserole
directions: Add vegetables to butter along with brown sugar and salt. Cook 5 minutes.
Place squash in greased casserole and stir in vegetable mixture.
Cover top with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cabbage hot dish
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Cut cabbage fine and layer 1/2 in bottom of baking dish.
Cover with rice and meat.
Top with cabbage.
Mix soup and water.
Pour over and cover.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 375°.

title: apple muffins
directions: Sweeten apples with 1/4 cup sugar; set aside.
Sift flour, salt, cinnamon, 1/4 cup sugar and baking powder.
Blend in egg, milk and oil.
Fold in chopped apple mixture.
Pour into greased muffin pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: passover dairy lasagna *
directions: In medium bowl, beat eggs.
Add cottage cheese, salt, pepper and garlic.
Mix well; wet matzo with milk until moist, not soggy.
Pour a little sauce in bottom of 8 x 8-inch baking pan. Layer remaining ingredients, alternating, matzo, cheese, tomato sauce and Muenster cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Let rest 5 to 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: honey dressing(great over fresh fruit)
directions: Mix together.
Beat with electric mixer or blender.
Add very slowly (or sugar will settle to bottom if added too fast) 1 quart oil until thick.
Keeps a long time in covered container.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix cake, one egg and 1 stick of butter together and pat smooth in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Then set aside.
Mix together cream cheese, 3 eggs, 1 box powdered sugar and vanilla.
Pour this over the first layer and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: lima pork chops
directions: Brown chops in oil.
Layer lima beans, soup, pepper, pork chops and onion in baking dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, or until tender.
Yields 4 servings.

title: poppin cereal bars
directions: Mix popcorn, cereal, pretzels and M&M's.
Melt marshmallows and butter.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut into squares.

title: seven layer christmas ribbon cake
directions: Mix as directed on box. Add different cake coloring to each layer. Can use 2 layers of green, red, chocolate and leave one plain as long as you alternate layers. Pour thin layers of batter onto 8-inch skillet, about enough to cover bottom of pan and bake in 500° to 550° oven for about 2 1/2 to 3 minutes per layer. Spray skillet with nonstick spray each time. An 8-inch cake pan may be used to cook layers.

title: sweet 'n hot beans
directions: Fry, or render bacon in suitable pot.
Add onions and cayenne and cook until half done.
Stir in sugar and beans; simmer a few moments before serving.
You may also use molasses instead of as much sugar as asked.
Serves two to four people.

title: milky way cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on box.
In double boiler, add 1 tablespoon butter and 3 chopped candy bars and melt. Add to cake batter.
Bake as directed on box.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine cheeses, onion, sauce and lemon juice and form a ball. Roll ball in chopped pecans.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: shrimp curry
directions: Blend butter, flour and seasonings.
Gradually stir in milk. Cook until thick and smooth, being careful to stir constantly. Add catsup and shrimp; heat.
Serve over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Boil cranberries, sugar and water for 10 minutes.
Add the Jell-O; stir well.
Let cool until warm.
Add celery, apples and walnuts; mix well.
Pour into mold.
Chill until firm.
Remove from mold onto lettuce leaves.

title: meatball stroganoff
directions: Mix together ground beef, bread crumbs, onions, egg and salt. Shape into 16 meatballs, brown in skillet and pour off grease.
Add soup, sour cream and 1/4 cup water.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir often.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Note:
Need one piece aluminum foil, 12 x 15-inches.

title: corey's sugar cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Add milk.
Stir in flour.
Drop dough out on cookie sheets.
Sprinkle cookies with sugar before baking.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 375°.

title: chimichangas
directions: Pour all ingredients over meat.
Bake at 300° overnight or until meat falls apart, 5 to 7 hours.
Remove all fat and bones from meat.
Shred meat and using a large slotted spoon, place a spoonful in the middle of a large flour tortilla.
(I buy from "El Molino's").
Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.
Roll up and close with toothpicks.
Using canola oil and electric skillet, fry until golden brown on both sides.
Serve with salsa and sour cream.

title: mushroom-filled meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, combine beef, milk, egg, bread pieces, parsley flakes, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and garlic powder; set aside.
In a small skillet, heat butter.
Add onion and mushrooms.
Cook and stir over medium heat until onion is tender.
Set aside.

title: grits and green chili pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bring water to a boil in medium saucepan.
Slowly stir in grits.
Simmer until thickened, about 3 to 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese, onions, egg and hot pepper sauce.
Arrange chilies in a 9-inch pie plate, spoke fashion, with larger ends against edges of plate and tips toward center.
Pour grits mixture evenly over chilies.
Bake 30 minutes or until set.
Let stand 5 minutes. Cut into wedges and serve warm.

title: annie's popovers
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, salt, eggs and milk.
Beat about 15 seconds with fork or eggbeater.
Grease 6 custard cups with vegetable shortening, including outside rims.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes or at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: lemon butter icing
directions: In small mixing bowl, whip butter. Alternately add lemon juice and sugar until smooth and creamy.

title: banana cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients (flour, baking powder, soda and salt) in a small bowl.
In a large bowl, cream the shortening and sugar. Add vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix flour into creamed mixture alternately with the buttermilk.
Stir in the bananas and pecans.
Pour into a well-greased and floured pan (13 x 9-inch rectangle pan or two 8-inch round layers).
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Suggest cream cheese icing.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Roll dough into a rectangle, 15 x 9-inches.
Spread with butter.
Mix sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over rectangle.
Roll up, beginning at wide side.
Pinch edge of dough into roll to seal well.
Stretch roll to make even.
Cut roll into 15 pieces.
Place slightly apart in greased muffin cups.
Let rise until double. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 400°.
While warm, frost rolls with icing.

title: caesar dressing
directions: Blend ingredients on high until well mixed.
Pour over Pepperoni Caesar Salad.

title: corn fritters
directions: Canned or fresh corn may be used.
Mix the corn pulp and the beaten egg yolks, flour and seasoning.
Add the stiffly beaten egg whites and blend.
Drop by spoonfuls the size of oyster on a hot buttered frying pan and brown.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, vanilla, oil and grated zucchini.
Mix flour, salt, soda and cinnamon together.
Add to egg mixture gradually.
Then add nuts and dates.
(If using dates, it is best to roll them in a little flour first to keep them from sticking together.)
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch).
Place mixture in greased pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Test center with toothpick for doneness. (Very good sliced and spread with cream cheese.)

title: brucholoni
directions: Preheat
oven
Place steaks on cutting board; trim fat.
If meat has a bone, cut straight below bone.
Pound steaks to
about
1/8 inch thick.
(Take care not to tear.) In medium bowl
combine
bread
crumbs, eggs, garlic and cheese. Pat mixture evenly over pounded steaks, leaving 1 inch border at edges.
Scatter
onion
and
green pepper over bread crumb mixture.
Top with hard-cooked eggs.

title: snowballs
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Add flour. Blend thoroughly and add nuts. Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Put on baking sheet and bake at 325° about 20 minutes.
Do not brown.
Cool.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta as directed on package and drain well.
Sprinkle Salad Supreme over pasta and mix well.
Add 2/3 of Italian dressing to pasta mixture and toss, covering well.
Add vegetables and toss gently.
Let stand overnight.
Add remainder of dressing; toss and serve.

title: fred's untossed salad
directions: Basically, use whatever you have, the greater the variety the better.
Cut all ingredients into 1/4 to 1/2-inch squares or cubes. Layer them in a large wooden bowl.
Lettuce on the bottom and any variety on top, layer on layer in an interesting and alternative manner.
Serve with tongs, going down side of bowl to bring out all ingredients in a mixed manner to serving bowls.
Have a variety of dressing on side.

title: rice dressing
directions: Cook rice in boiling water and salt, until dry.
Chop onion, put in rice with eggs and parsley.
Heat cheese in milk and oil over low heat until cheese melts.
Bake in covered dish at 350° for 30 minutes.
Stir 2 or 3 times.
Uncover and bake 10 to 15 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix juice from fruit cocktail plus water to make 1 cup.
Mix vanilla and fruit cocktail into juice mixture.
Mix sugar, flour, baking soda and eggs together.
Add dry ingredients into wet. Stir well.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup nuts.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan at 350°.

title: doretta's spread
directions: Blend
cream
cheese
with
brown
sugar, green pepper, Worcestershire
sauce,
grated onion and walnuts.
After thoroughly	blended,
add green grapes.
Use your own judgement as to amount of green grapes.	Serve as a spread for crackers.

title: stroganoff
directions: Brown onion in butter.
Stir in ground beef.
Brown well.
Add flour and salt.
Add mushrooms; saute for 5 minutes.
Add mushroom soup; simmer for 10 minutes.
Add sour cream just before serving, to meat.
Put sauce over noodles.

title: fettucini roberto
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter and oil on high heat.
Reduce heat and add ham and peas.
Cook noodles and drain.
Add 4 tablespoons butter and cheeses to noodles.
Add cream and then mushroom mix. Serve hot.

title: gas house eggs(recommended for children to prepare)
directions: Cut out center of bread with biscuit cutter.
Place bread and centers in well-buttered, hot skillet.
"Squeeze" butter the top side of bread.
Gently break an egg in center of bread.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until egg is partially cooked and turn over.
Turn the centers over, too.
Serve them with jelly!

title: buttermilk sherbet
directions: Mix buttermilk, sugar, salt, pineapple and vanilla.
Freeze to a mush about 45 minutes.
Whip egg white until stiff and fold into well-beaten mixture.
Return to freezer and freeze without stirring.

title: corn casserole
directions: Put melted butter in the bottom of a large, shallow baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients together in a large bowl and pour into baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes or until firm and slightly browned.

title: cherry winks
directions: Combine flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Cream butter, lemon peel, vanilla and sugar.
Add egg and milk.
Beat thoroughly.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop from teaspoon, small balls into crushed cornflakes.
Arrange on a greased cookie sheet and top with cherry halves.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: yogurt popsicles
directions: Combine ingredients and freeze in popsicle molds or small waxed paper cups (with sticks inserted into cups).

title: fudge
directions: Mix butter or margarine in double boiler.
Combine sugar and milk in saucepan and bring to a slow boil.
Boil 6 minutes. Combine chocolate chips and nuts in mixing bowl.
Add hot mixtures to chips and nuts; beat.
Pour into greased pan.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Combine sugar, flour and juice; heat over low heat until some of the sugar melts.
Stir in pineapple and cheese.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish, place the crushed crackers on top and drizzle margarine over the crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Mix together cream cheese and 10x sugar; set aside.
In separate bowl, add pudding and milk.
Beat 2 1/2 minutes.
Let stand 1 minute, then add to cream mixture.
Add vanilla and Cool Whip.
Crush Oreo cookies.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, place crushed cookies.
Add layer of creamed mixture.
Add more crushed cookies, another layer of creamed mixture and top with crushed cookies. Chill.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Place chicken in deep heavy pot.
Add water, wine, salt, onion and celery.
Cover and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from heat.
Strain broth.
Refrigerate chicken and broth at once without cooling.
When cool, remove meat from bones.
Cut into pieces.
Rinse mushrooms and pat dry. Reserve enough whole caps to garnish top.
Slice and saute remaining mushrooms in butter until brown.
Measure broth.
Use as part of liquid for cooking rice following directions for firm rice on package.
Combine chicken, mushrooms and rice in 4-quart casserole.
Blend in sour cream and mushroom soup.
Mix with chicken rice mixture.
Arrange reserved mushroom caps in circle over casserole.
Cover.
May refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: uncle billy's fudge
directions: Stir until creamy.
Pour into buttered jelly roll pan.
Cool in the refrigerator and cut into squares.
Makes approximately 5 pounds.

title: spicy whole wheat zucchini muffins
directions: In a medium size mixing bowl, mix flours, wheat germ, sugar, baking powder and soda, spices and salt.
Set aside.
Pour milk in a 2-cup measuring cup.
Add egg and oil and blend well.
Pour milk mixture over dry ingredients; add zucchini and raisins.
Stir just enough to moisten.
Do not overmix.
Spoon batter into greased muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 22 minutes.

title: oreo cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish, mix crushed cookies and margarine.
Press to form a crust.
Mix cream cheese and confectioners sugar with mixer until creamy, then blend in 1 container of Cool Whip.
Spread over Oreo crust.
Mix both puddings with milk until thickened.
Spread over cream cheese mixture. Spread other container of Cool Whip over pudding.
Refrigerate.

title: zucchini loaf
directions: Mix all
ingredients
and spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: summer fruit and cheese mold
directions: Early in day or a day ahead:
Place raspberries in refrigerator to thaw slightly.

title: nut roll #2
directions: Mix all ingredients together, leaving enough cracker crumbs to roll it in.
Roll in cracker crumbs, forming into logs (large or small).
Keep refrigerated; slice off as needed.

title: buckeyes
directions: Blend sugar, peanut butter, margarine, salt and vanilla until smooth. Shape into 1-inch balls. Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in top of double boiler. Dip balls in chocolate mixture with toothpick until 3/4 covered. Place on waxed paper until set. Cover over hole until smooth. Makes 6 dozen.

title: corn bread
directions: Cook cornmeal, water and salt until thick.
Add milk, flour and sugar.
Add baking powder, butter and eggs.
Mix well.
Pour into greased cast-iron skillet, 9 or 10-inch.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large saucepan or microwave melt butter and chocolate.
Add remaining bar ingredients, mix well.
Spread in pan.

title: heath candy bars
directions: Line a large cookie sheet with foil, well buttered.
Place crackers on foil.
Bring margarine and sugar to a boil.
Boil 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Bake at 375° for 7 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with chips.
Spread evenly when melted. Sprinkle with nuts.
Cut or break apart when cool.

title: freeze and bake rolls
directions: In a large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Add 2 teaspoons sugar; let stand for 5 minutes.
Add milk, oil, salt and remaining sugar.
Add enough flour to form a stiff dough.
Turn out onto a floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic, about 6 to 8 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning once to grease top. Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled, about 1 1/2 hours. Punch dough down.
Divide into four pieces.
Cover three pieces with plastic wrap.
Divide one piece into 12 balls.
To form knots, roll each ball into a 10-inch rope, tie into a knot and pinch ends together.
Repeat with remaining dough.
Place rolls on greased baking sheet; brush with melted butter.
Cover and let rise until doubled, about 20 to 30 minutes.
To serve immediately, bake at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes.
To freeze, partially bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Allow to cool.
Freeze.
Reheat frozen rolls at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In a medium saucepan, mix sugar, margarine, cocoa, milk and vanilla.
Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add quick oats and peanut butter.
Mix well and drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Cool and enjoy!

title: apple crisp
directions: Cut apples up.
Put in baking dish.
Mix rest of ingredients together and put on top of apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 45 minutes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Squeeze lemons; mix Eagle Brand milk with egg yolks and then mix with lemon juice.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill for a few hours.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Butter shallow baking dish. Place in dish 1/2 of crumbs blended with butter. Add layer of oysters. Pour over content 1/2 of liquid. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Repeat layers. End with crumbs on top. Bake at 450° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients and make patties.
Fry in vegetable oil.

title: braised steak(dee-licious)
directions: Blend together honey, vinegar and Kitchen Bouquet.
Place meat in large glass baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Marinate in mixture in refrigerator 2 to 4 hours (covered).
Turn frequently.
Brown meat on both sides in large heavy frying pan in oil.
Add mushroom liquid (from only 1 can) to catsup.
Add to marinade.
Pour around meat.
Cook tightly covered over low heat until tender, 1 to 2 hours.
Add mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes.
Remove meat and mushrooms; thicken liquid with flour (or cornstarch) and water for gravy.

title: angel food surprise
directions: Break up angel food cake and place in square pan.
Mix vanilla pudding and pour over cake.
Pour cherry pie filling and spread over pudding.
Cover with Cool Whip.

title: potato balls(8 servings)
directions: Place cooled, mashed potatoes in a covered bowl overnight in refrigerator.
Put potatoes in bowl and add flour, egg, bread crumbs and salt.
Mix well.

title: baked stuffed mushrooms with ricotta
directions: Wipe the mushrooms.
Remove the stems and finely chop them. Mix the mushrooms with the bread crumbs, garlic, parsley, eggs, Ricotta, grated cheese, salt and pepper.
Fill each mushroom cap with the stuffing.
Place on a shallow pan.
Drizzle olive oil over each one.
Bake on highest rack in a preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: garlic bread
directions: Warm the olive oil, garlic and salt and pepper in a small pan. Cut the bread in slices, then brush the heated mixture in each slit and cover with silver foil.
Cook at 350° for 15 minutes and serve.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt oleo.
Place in large pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour over melted butter.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: creamed vegetables
directions: Bring the last 4 ingredients to a boil and add vegetables to sauce.
Boil 5 minutes, then bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Drain.

title: two loaves bread(quick)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add shortening, salt, sugar and half the flour.
Beat 2 minutes at medium mixer speed.
Add remaining flour and blend with spoon until smooth.
Cover with cloth and let raise for 30 minutes.
Beat 255 strokes and spread it evenly in greased pans.
Let raise 45 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: banana milk shake
directions: Combine ingredients
in a blender and mix until frothy. Serve at once.
Yields
serving, approximately 180 calories per serving.

title: company carrots
directions: Cook carrots until slightly done.
Slice long ways in strips and place in baking dish.
Pour sauce made of the last 5 ingredients over carrot strips.
Top with butter or margarine, bread cubes then sprinkle with paprika and parsley.
