Bake qt 350° to 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated but not too soft.

title: texas rice
directions: In 3-quart casserole, combine water, uncooked rice, soup mix and onion.
Put in microwave for 4 to 5 minutes or until boiling. Let stand, covered, 5 minutes.
Stir before serving.

title: no peek stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a casserole or roaster. Cook at 250° for 5 to 6 hours.
Do not peek.

title: raw vegetable salad
directions: Cut the ingredients, except dressing, into bite-size pieces. Mix with salad dressing.
Marinate about 2 hours before serving.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and chill 24 hours before serving.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Sprinkle nuts and coconut in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix according to box directions and pour over nuts and coconut.
Mix cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar.
Mix well and spoon on cake batter.
Drop on top of cake batter, making rows; do not spread.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven until cake mix part is done.
As cake cools, cream cheese mixture will sink. "Earthquake."

title: white chili
directions: Soak beans, drain.
Combine beans, broth, onion, garlic, chillis, oregano, cumin, red pepper, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in chicken and simmer (covered) 1/2 hour to 1 hour more.
Before serving, stir in cheese just until melted.

title: golden ambrosia pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients (except pecans and coconut) in large bowl, mixing well.
Stir in pecans and coconut.
Pour mixture into unbaked 9-inch pastry shell.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes at 350° until crust is golden and center is set. Cool completely on wire rack.
Makes 8 servings.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cheese and blend all ingredients in blender or with electric mixer.

title: cheese-squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and drain.
Mash squash; add cream cheese, beaten eggs and 3/4 cup grated American cheese.
Blend and place in greased casserole.
Mix remaining 1/4 cup grated cheese with crackers crumbs.
Spread over casserole and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water; add pie filling and stir.
Add 1/2 cup cold water and drained fruit.
Pour in oblong dish and chill until set (do not mold).
Top with mixture of Cool Whip and sour cream (1/2 carton medium size Cool Whip and equal amount of sour cream).

title: meringue cookies
directions: Beat first 2 ingredients until frothy.
Add sugar, a little at a time.
Beat until stiff peaks form.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake on brown paper in a 325° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: beefy baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef; drain off all fat.
Combine with all ingredients.
Arrange bacon on top in 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Cream together cheese and mayonnaise.
Add pineapple, drained of all juice.
Cut marshmallows in small pieces; add to above mixture.
Whip cream stiff and add with cherries cut in pieces. Put in refrigerator tray in freezing compartment.
Let stand 8 to 12 hours.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Boil sugar, butter and milk together for 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in chocolate chips and marshmallow cream.
Stir until smooth.
Add nuts if desired.
Pour into buttered 9 x 11-inch pan.
When cold, cut into squares. Yields 5 pounds.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Cream together butter, brown sugar, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Add flour, baking soda, salt and mix well.
Add M&M's; stir.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet and bake in 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: creamy cucumber salad ring
directions: Dissolve gelatine and sugar in hot water.
Add cream cheese, mayonnaise, horseradish and salt.
Beat until smooth in mixer. Add lemon juice.
Chill about 30 minutes.
Stir in cucumbers and onions.
Pour into 1-quart ring and chill until firm.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Add flour and seasonings.
Fold in Rice Krispies.
Shape into small balls and place on cookie sheet. Flatten with fork.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 50.

title: old fashion chocolate fudge
directions: Pour
sugar
and
milk in heavy saucepan and stir until sugar is	dissolved.
Heat
to boiling, then take out 1 cup of the syrup
and	dissolve the cocoa in it.
Return to saucepan and cook until it reaches a temperature of 238° or until soft ball stage. Remove and cool.
When cold add vanilla and salt. Beat
until creamy
and
dull.	Add
nuts and turn on buttered dish.
Cut into squares.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Form into balls.
Brown in oil. Remove balls to casserole.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water; add lemon juice.
Blend flour with remaining fat in skillet.
Slowly add bouillon mixture.
Pour mixture over meat balls.
Add bay leaves.
Cover and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Heat sugar, syrup and vanilla. Do not let boil.
Add cereals. Press into buttered 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: waffles with chicken and gravy
directions: Put chicken broth in pan.
Add cut up chicken (cooked).
When hot, thicken with flour and water.
Add salt to taste.
Turn heat to low.

title: oriental chicken wings
directions: Cut chicken wings in half.
Discard tips.
Place in baking pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour soy sauce and oil over wing pieces.
Dot with butter.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Uncover.
Add ginger and marmalade.
Return for 10 minutes.
Turn wings.
Return for 10 more minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot.

title: cream of turkey wild rice soup
directions: In a large pan, cook and stir mushrooms, celery and peppers in margarine until tender.
Mix flour and broth together until blended.
Gradually add to vegetables.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and thickens.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk, rice, turkey and cream cheese.
Blend well.
Bring to a boil.
Heat over low, stirring.
Makes 8 (1 cup) servings.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add vanilla.
Stir in flour, blending well.
Stir in nuts.
Mix well.
Shape in teaspoonfuls of dough into balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: baked chicken
directions: Mix crumbs, cheese, parsley and garlic.
Dip chicken in butter. Salt and pepper chicken, then roll in crumb mixture.
Place in baking dish and pour remaining butter over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Don't turn over.

title: apple and sweet potato scallop
directions: Layer half of apples and sweet potatoes in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle sugar on this.
Spread raisins over this.
Repeat with other half of apples and potatoes.
Sprinkle spices.
Dot with margarine.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake until apples are soft and top is browned.

title: irene's oatmeal pie
directions: Stir the beaten eggs into milk.
Add the syrup and melted margarine.
Stir in the rest of the ingredients.
Pour into uncooked pie crust.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately one hour.

title: spaghetti and meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, bread crumbs, cheese, parsley, garlic and salt, using milk only to moisten and fry formed balls in oil. Remove from heat and cook onion until tender. Add remaining ingredients and simmer 30 minutes. Remove bay leaves. Add meatballs. Cook spaghetti as directions instructs.

title: cowboy caviar
directions: Mix well.
Serve with chips or as taco salad.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: Mix boiling water, cold water, jello and pie filling together, put in a deep dish and let set until firm.

title: marble squares
directions: Combine softened cream cheese & 1/3 c. sugar, mixing until well blended. Add egg; mixing well. Separately combine margarine, water, & chocolate squares in sauce pan; bring to boil; then remove from heat. Add eggs (2), sour cream, soda, & salt; mix well.Pour into greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 jelly roll pan. Spoon cream cheese mixture over chocolate batter.
Cut through batter with a knife several times for marble effect. Sprinkle with chocolate chips. Bake at 375° for 25-30 minutes.

title: lusty italian dip
directions: In a small mixing bowl, mix the sour cream with the dry spaghetti sauce powder until well blended.
Add instant onion. You can use fresh onion or chopped green onion if you prefer.
Mix thoroughly.
Store in refrigerator for several hours before serving.
Good with veggies or crackers.

title: devil dogs
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Combine all cookie ingredients together in a large bowl; mix well. Drop by tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 425° for 7 to 8 minutes. Let cool.

title: breakfast burrito
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Put turkey burger in frying pan.
When it starts to brown, put eggs in, then start sauteing the onions in butter.
Toss the eggs and burger around until the eggs are done. Then add cheese to eggs and burger.
When cheese is melted enough, take off burner.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Boil sugar and water to 238°.
Pour over stiffly beaten egg whites.
Continue beating until candy stiffens.
When nearly set, drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: peanut date cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugars and peanut butter.
Add eggs, water and vanilla and beat until creamy.
Sift flour, salt and baking soda together into creamy mixture and blend well.
Mix in oats and dates.
Drop teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 or 15 minutes.

title: catalina chicken
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole dish.
Mix all ingredients together and pour over chicken.
Cover pan with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown and tender.

title: cheddar pecan cheese ball
directions: Bring cheese to room temperature.
Beat all ingredients, but pecans, with electric mixer.
Shape into 1 large or 2 small balls. Roll balls in chopped pecans.
Chill.

title: orange cake
directions: Finely shred enough orange peel to make 1 tablespoon.
Set aside.
Remove and discard the remaining peel.
Section oranges. Set aside.
In a small mixing bowl, stir together vanilla pudding and orange liqueur.
Cut the pound cake into 12 slices.
Place 2 slices on each of 6 individual dessert plates.
Top each serving with some orange sections and pudding-liqueur mixture.
Sprinkle with reserved orange peel.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Combine sugar and milk in saucepan.
Bring to boil and cook until mixture will form a soft ball in water (test in spoon). Remove from burner and add vanilla, butter and peanut butter.
Mix until ingredients start to thicken.
Pour into buttered cake pan and spread evenly.
Cut into squares when cooled.

title: possum
directions: Scald opossom in lye water and scrape off hair; do not break skin.
Dress whole, leaving head and tail.
Rinse thoroughly.
Rub inside and out with salt.
Let stand in cool place overnight.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Dissolve yeast in 1 1/2 cups lukewarm water.
Add sugar and salt; stir until dissolved.
Add flour; mix well.
Turn out dough on floured board; knead for about 5 minutes. Roll into thin strips; shape into pretzels.
Place on well-greased cookie sheet.
Beat egg yolk with one tablespoon of water; brush on pretzels.
Sprinkle generously with coarse salt. Bake in oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sausage and cornbread pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cook sausage and 1 cup onions in a large skillet until pork is brown; drain and return to skillet.
Add soup and next 4 ingredients.

Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes. Spoon mixture into greased 3-quart casserole. Combine baking mix and remaining ingredients. Spread over sausage mixture. Bake 15 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center of topping comes out clean.
Makes 6 servings.

title: meatless meatballs with mushroom sauce
directions: Pour over bread.
Cover and keep in refrigerator overnight. In the morning, melt 1/4 pound butter or margarine; pour over bread/egg mixture.
Cover with crushed corn flakes.
Bake uncovered 1 hour at 350°.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Makes 8 servings.
I serve with fresh fruit and hot cinnamon rolls.
The mess is gone before you cook it!

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic until done.
Drain.
Add sauces and soup to meat mixture.
Mix well and heat.
Layer, starting with meat mixture, then add a layer of corn tortillas.
Repeat layers until all is used, using the meat mixture last.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted. Serve while hot.

title: vanilla cream sauce
directions: In a 1-quart saucepan, boil sugar and water to 238°, or until a little forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Pour syrup slowly on egg yolks while beating.
Continue beating until creamy.
Chill.
Add vanilla.
Whip cream and fold in.
Makes 8 servings.

title: doritos mexi casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients, then add Doritos.
Mix and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Mix avocados with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix.

title: pumpkin dream bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat margarine and 1/3 cup sugar until fluffy.
Add combined oats and flour; mix well.
Spread evenly onto bottom of prepared pan.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool slightly.
Beat cream cheese and 1 cup sugar at medium speed until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add remaining ingredients; mix until smooth.
Pour over partially cooled crust. Bake an additional 45 to 50 minutes or until center appears set. Serve with whipped cream.

title: hot rolls
directions: Cream lard, sugar, salt and beat egg slightly.
Add to flour and hot water.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Use enough flour to make a soft dough, about 2 pounds or 1 1/2 quarts.
Makes 2 dozen rolls.

title: pork chop casserole(ingredients for 1 person)
directions: Place raw pork
chop
in heavy iron skillet or casserole and sprinkle with
salt
and
pepper.
Sprinkle
rice over top; layer of onion,
pepper rings and tomato.
Pour juice over all. Add Worcestershire sauce.
Cover
and bake 1 hour at 400°.
Fix as many as needed.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix vanilla pudding and water.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add strawberry jello.
Let cool. Slice strawberries.
Put in pie plate.
Pour mixture over strawberries.
Refrigerate.

title: sweet potato pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: In a mixing bowl, mix all ingredients.
Beat on medium speed with a hand mixer.
Pour into 2 deep pie crusts and bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Fry bacon to crisp. Drain and reserve drippings.
Shred cabbage, shred carrots, julienne potatoes and slice onions.
Put 3 to 4 tablespoons of drippings plus 2 tablespoons butter in skillet.
Set to medium heat.

Place onions in skillet and then mix remaining ingredients and place on top. Cover and let simmer for several minutes. Remove cover and toss occasionally until tender-crisp. When finished, crumble bacon and place on top.

title: hamburger noodle bake
directions: In a large skillet, cook beef, onions and green peppers, half at a time, until meat is brown.
Drain off fat.
Cook noodles according to package directions; drain well.
Return drained noodles to kettle.
Stir in meat mixture, tomato soup, cheese, chili sauce, pimento, salt, chili powder, pepper and 2 cups of water; mix well. Divide mixture between two 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dishes.
Toss bread crumbs with melted butter; sprinkle atop casseroles.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: granola(great snack or cereal)
directions: Mix well. Spread on a cookie sheet and bake at 250° to 300° for about 40 minutes. (Add dried fruit: cranberries, prunes, apricots, etc. keeping the overall measurements the same.) Store in airtight container.

title: potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on. Cool and peel. Quarter like mashed potatoes. Put into 9 x 13 glass pan. Add onion, salt and pepper to taste. Add 1 cup mayonnaise. Stir well. Brown your bacon; drain and sprinkle over potatoes. Add cheese over the bacon. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetarian lasagne
directions: Mix tomato paste and water in saucepan.
Heat, stirring, until well blended.
Remove from heat.
Beat eggs in large bowl. Add Ricotta or cottage cheese and spinach.
Lightly grease bottom of a 13
x9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover bottom of dish with a little sauce, layer of uncooked noodles, half of spinach/cheese mixture and half of sauce.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover dish with a lightly greased sheet of aluminum foil. Bake at 350° in a preheated oven for 60 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: refreshing spiced tea
directions: Combine tea and spices.
Pour boiling water over them.	Cover and steep 5 minutes.
Strain into 2-quart pitcher.	Add sugar and cool.
Add juices and water.
Chill.
Serve over ice and garnish with lemon slices.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Set aside. Beat butter until fluffy. Gradually add peel and sugar, then add egg yolks and mix thoroughly. Add dry ingredients to butter mixture alternately with sour cream. Beat egg whites until stiff, then fold into batter.
Pour into an 8-inch round cake pan (greased and floured).
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Let cool 15 minutes, then turn onto a platter and cut into 2 layers.

title: zuppa povera
directions: Boil rice in 1 1/2 cups water and set aside.
Heat marrow, then add onion and celery and cook to wilt down.
Add 2 cups fresh spinach.
Cover and cook down.
Add tomatoes and cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Then add chicken broth and water, tomato paste, salt, pepper and parsley.
Cover.
Raise heat and cook 5 minutes.
Add rice and cover and cook until it comes to a slow boil.
Crack eggs into soup and cook a few minutes to poach.
Don't let eggs touch. Top with fresh Romano cheese when serving.

title: shady maple granola
directions: Combine dry ingredients (omit raisins).
Combine liquid ingredients and add wet to dry, mixing thoroughly.
Bake in shallow, oiled pan for 20 to 30 minutes in slow oven at 300° or until toasted to taste.
When cool, mix in raisins or other dried fruit.
Store in dry, cool place.

title: cherry biscuits
directions: Mix everything together and pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until golden.
Slice into thin strips (1 x 3-inch) and place on a greased cookie sheet. Bake for 15 minutes more to harden and make golden on the sides.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add all ingredients (except 1/2 cup flour, raisins and nuts).
Mix well.
Roll raisins and nuts in 1/2 cup flour and add to mixture.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325° (maybe longer).
Test with toothpick.
Bake in tube pan lined in bottom with greased wax paper.

title: pecan delights
directions: Cream butter and shortening with sugar and salt.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Mix.
Add flour, and blend well.
Take one teaspoon of dough at a time.
Shape into a ball, place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown (15 to 20 minutes).
Roll in powdered sugar.
Cool and roll in sugar again.

title: buh-trash
directions: In electric skillet, brown meat with onion. Drain.
Add tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Add cooked pasta shells.
Season to taste.

title: family favorite shrimp casserole
directions: Marinate shrimp in oil and lemon juice for 2 hours. Cook rice about half done. Saute peppers and onions in butter very slowly for 15 minutes. Mix all ingredients. Pour into casserole. Top with almonds and bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: spicy turkey and eggplant chili
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add eggplant, onion, chili powder and cayenne pepper and cook until vegetables are tender, stirring frequently, about 7 minutes.
Add turkey and cook until no longer pink, breaking up with back of spoon, about 5 minutes.
Add all beans, tomato sauce, celery, bell pepper, garlic and cumin.
Bring to simmer.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes, stirring frequently.
Chili can be prepared 1 day ahead.
Cover and refrigerate.
Rewarm over medium heat, stirring frequently. Ladle chili into bowls and serve.

title: mexican salad
directions: Put ingredients together.
Add Fritos before serving.

title: popeye pancakes
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix in blender the eggs, flour, milk and salt.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 425° to 450° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top.
Cut and serve.

title: oreo pie
directions: Melt butter in baking pan.
Crumble cookies and spread over butter for first layer.
(Save a few cookies for top.)
Spread soft ice cream over cookie crumbs.

title: reuben sandwiches(open faced)
directions: Toast 1 slice bread for each sandwich.
Spread with Thousand Island dressing.
Top with slices of corned beef, then well drained sauerkraut, adding more dressing between meat and sauerkraut.
Top with slices of Swiss cheese.
Place on cookie sheet and bake in oven at 450° until hot.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift first 6 ingredients and set aside.
Mix together oil, eggs, water and pumpkin in large bowl until smooth.
Mix sifted ingredients into beaten mixture.
Pour into 2 pans sprayed with nonstick spray and bake 1 hour at 350° or until toothpick comes out clean.
(Four large soup cans sprayed and filled 2/3 full yields round loaves.)

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Beat potato until creamy.
Then mix 2 eggs, 1 teaspoon vanilla and Eagle Brand milk with the creamed sweet potatoes.
Then mix brown sugar, flour and nuts.
Sprinkle mixture on top of potatoes and dot with butter.
Cook 45 minutes at 250°.

title: chili cheese casserole
directions: Place a layer of chilies and a layer of cheeses.
Repeat.

title: potato beef meal
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add all other ingredients.
Place in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 1 to 2 minutes more, until cheese melts.

title: frozen lemon yogurt souffle
directions: With electric mixer, whip the sugar and yogurt together; add vanilla and lemon.
Fold in beaten egg whites and whipped milk. Turn into individual sherbet dishes and freeze.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Place a single layer of sliced strawberries in bottom and up the sides of a trifle bowl or other large, clear bowl.
Sprinkle berries with 2 tablespoons of granulated sugar.

title: coconut chess pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour; add eggs and stir in vanilla. Melt butter and add to mixture. Fold in coconut and milk and mix well. Pour mixture into unbaked shells. Bake in preheated 450° oven for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 to 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: blueberry surprise
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix graham cracker crumbs, margarine and confectioners sugar together and pack into bottom of a 10 x 13-inch dish.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix pumpkin, evaporated milk, sugars, eggs and spices together. Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Take dry cake mix and sprinkle over pumpkin mixture.
Knife into the batter.
Add walnuts.
Melt butter and pour over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni. Rinse, drain well and let cool. Mix all ingredients in mixing bowl. Pour Italian Dressing over and stir. Cover and refrigerate overnight for best flavor. Stir again just before serving.

title: rice and sausage casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch dish.
Combine first 7 ingredients; pour into dish.
Brown sausage.
Crumble on top.
Cover with foil and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Stir well when removed from oven.
Add soy sauce and mushrooms; stir in.
Return to oven for 30 minutes. Garnish with parsley.

title: rave reviews coconut cake
directions: Blend cake mix, pudding mix, water, eggs and oil in large mixer bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Stir in coconut and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until tester in middle comes out clean.
Let cool 15 minutes and frost with Coconut Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: chocolate amaretto cheesecake
directions: Sprinkle 1/4 cup crumbs on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan sprayed with Pam.
Set remaining crumbs aside.

title: tuna salad
directions: Drain water out of tuna and place into a large bowl to add other ingredients.
Add celery salt, onion salt and a pinch of salt and pepper.
Mix well, until tuna is broken into smaller pieces.
Then add mayonnaise and mustard.
Stir well until thoroughly mixed.
Chill and serve on a lettuce leaf.

title: reuben casserole
directions: About 45 minutes before serving:
Preheat oven to 400°.
In a 9 x 9-inch baking dish, stir sauerkraut with its liquid and salad dressing.
Top with a layer of corned beef.
Bake for 15 minutes, until bubbly.
Remove dish from oven.
Place cheese on top of meat in a single layer.
Top with a layer of bread.
Lightly brush bread with butter.
Bake 10 minutes longer, or until bread is crisp.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Melt margarine in pie pan.
Add cracker crumbs to form crust. Now add pecans, coconut and chocolate chips.
Top with Eagle Brand milk.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Chill before serving.
Top with Cool Whip (optional).

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine in casserole.
Place chicken in layers with onions and mushrooms.
Cook, covered, for 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Remove chicken; add enough boiling water to mushroom liquid to make 4 1/2 cups of broth in casserole.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in broth.
Add rice; replace chicken and cook, covered, for 1 hour.

title: easy lemon pound cake
directions: Beat
for
minutes
with mixer, scraping bowl often. Bake in tube pan at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: unbelievable peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat egg.
Add vanilla.
Mix in sugar and stir well.
Stir in peanut butter until completely blended. With a teaspoon, form balls about 1-inch in diameter and place on slightly greased cookie sheet, not too close together.
Do not flatten.
Bake in a 325° oven for 13 to 15 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Cool slightly before removing from pan onto wax paper.

title: simple corn pudding
directions: Grease casserole and pour in 2 cans of corn.
Blend in the two well beaten eggs.
Mix flour and sugar, then blend into corn mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: tuna lasagna
directions: Cook the noodles according to package directions. Drain tuna and mix with sour cream, milk, mushroom soup, salt and pepper. Grease casserole dish and layer the mixture with noodles beginning with tuna. Mix the bread crumbs, cheese and melted butter. Sprinkle the mixture over the casserole. Bake uncovered at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water, then add cold water.
Stir in orange sherbet and oranges. Make sure sherbet is dissolved. Refrigerate until set.

title: canned soup
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large stock pot and bring to a boil. Continue to cook for 45 minutes.
Ladle into hot, sterile quart jars.
Seal and process in a hot water bath for about 15 minutes.

title: pizzelles
directions: Heat pizzelle iron during mixing of ingredients.
Mix all ingredients in order given.
Add flour slowly.
Drop tablespoons onto iron and bake until golden brown.
Remove and cool flat on paper towels.
Makes about 45 cookies.

title: potato casserole
directions: Pour some butter into a casserole after mixing.
Melt 1/2 stick butter.
Mix corn flakes and butter together.
Crush corn flakes.
Put corn flakes on top of casserole.

title: lemon butter sauce
directions: Combine ingredients in 2 cup glass measure and place in oven. Cook High 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir sauce.
Serve immediately with seafood or hot green vegetables.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix the cream cheese, mayo and sugar until well creamed.
Add whole cranberry sauce, pineapple and nuts.
Mix well.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch glass container and freeze overnight.

title: texas cake
directions: Bring to boil the first 3 ingredients.
Add sugar, flour, baking soda and salt.
Beat eggs; add to mixture.
Stir in buttermilk and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes in a large jelly roll pan, greased.

title: chocolate chipper champs
directions: Beat together butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Gradually add combined flour, soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in candies and nuts.

title: blender custard pie
directions: Put above ingredients in blender.
Blend 1 minute on medium speed.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a well-greased and floured pan.

title: exotic celery casserole
directions: Cook celery in boiling salted water, just 5 minutes.
Drain and put in casserole with rest of ingredients.
Bake in uncovered 1 3/4-quart casserole dish for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: half time party dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in pan.
Top with chili, cheese and onion. Microwave for 3 plus minutes.
Serve warm with taco chips.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Cream together Crisco and flour in a bowl.
Add salt and enough cold water to make ingredients cling together, about 6 to 8 tablespoons.
Roll out dough on floured surface until dough is very thin.
Cut up oleo and place it in a 12 x 13-inch pan.
In a separate bowl, combine sugar, salt and flour and mix well.
Add cherries,
1 cup water and food coloring and mix well.
Pour mixture over oleo and top with crust.
Bake at 350° until crust browns.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Saute meat, breaking it into small particles as it browns. Drain, then add spaghetti sauce, water, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon oregano and simmer 15 minutes.
Cook noodles, as directed. Prepare a filling by mixing cheeses, eggs, 1/2 teaspoon salt, pepper and 1/8 teaspoon oregano together.
Put a small amount of sauce in bottom of greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Alternate with layers of noodles, cheese filling, noodles, meat sauce, etc.
Cover with sauce, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add seasoning.
Cut up lettuce, tomatoes for salad on a plate, put chips.
Top with lettuce.
Add hamburger.
Top with tomatoes and cheese.
Add hot sauce.
Add salad dressing.

title: south of the border appetizer
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake
in	a
lightly
greased 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crock-pot lasagne
directions: Brown meats and drain; add remaining ingredients and mix well. Cook noodles until tender; drain.
Toss with 2 tablespoons of oil.
Add to other ingredients in crock-pot and mix.
Cook on high for 1 hour, then on low for 2 hours or cook for 4 hours on low.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine beef, spaghetti sauce, chili powder, garlic powder, onion powder and water; boil for 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook macaroni in boiling water until tender; add peas and corn.
Mix both the macaroni combination and beef combination together.
Pour into baking dish; spread cheese on top; bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese-garlic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix Bisquick, milk, cheese and 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder until soft dough.
Beat for 30 seconds. Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with a little garlic powder.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes, until golden brown.
Mix margarine and 1/4 teaspoon garlic powder; brush over warm biscuits.
Makes 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: meat loaf(microwave)
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Put in microwave dish or pan. May spread 2 tablespoons catsup, steak, barbecue or chili sauce on top.

Cook on High power 12 to 18 minutes for a round shape, 8 to 13 minutes ring shape, 13 to 18 minutes loaf shape or 10 to 13 minutes for 6 (6-ounce) individual custard cups (arrange in a ring in the oven).
Rotate after 1/2 the cooking time.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes to complete cooking and become firm.

title: caramel-nut bars
directions: Combine flour, sugar and egg; cut in 1/2 cup margarine until crumbly.
Stir in walnuts.
Reserve 2 cups crumbs and press the rest into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Melt caramels with milk and 1/4 cup margarine.
Pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until bubbly.
Cool and cut into bars.
Store at room temperature.
Makes 24 to 36 bars.

title: microwave baked apples
directions: Put 1/2 of apples in micro-dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 dry ingredients. Add remaining apples and rest of dry ingredients.
Put 2 tablespoons brown sugar over top and dot with butter.
Microwave on High for 6 minutes.
Push apples down in syrup and microwave for 6 more minutes.
Dot with marshmallows.
Cover and let melt.

title: alana's chili(yields 6 servings)
directions: Cut pepper into slices and then small pieces.
Slice and cut onion.
Saute gently for 5 minutes in pan.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet.
Saute onions over medium heat until soft, about 5 minutes.
Add spinach and continue to cook, stirring often, until no liquid is left in skillet.
Add salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Stir well and allow to cool slightly, about 5 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix cornmeal, salt, onion, cheese, peppers, milk and egg.
Add corn; mix well.
Pour half batter into large iron skillet; add cooked beef, then pour remaining batter over beef.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: spinach salad
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Blend flour, paprika, salt and sugar into bacon grease.
Add onion, water and vinegar.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Arrange spinach in bowl; top with bacon and egg.
Add sauce and toss.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Layer twice the hamburger, macaroni, sauce, pepperoni and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: butter cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. In a large mixing bowl, cream the butter and sugar together. Add the sour cream and mix until incorporated. Sift the baking soda and flour together. Add to the creamed mixture alternating with eggs, beating after each addition. Add the vanilla and pour the mixture into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake for 1 hour 20 minutes.

title: artichoke-rice salad
directions: Cook rice in broth and cool.
Combine reserved marinade with curry, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Pour over rice mixture and mix in other ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: pecan mousse
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Scald milk over boiling water. Add softened gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Chill.
In the meantime, brown pecans in margarine and cool.
Beat milk very stiff, fold in nuts, vanilla and sugar.
Freeze until firm.

title: date bran chews
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Blend milk and lemon juice.
Combine with bran mixture.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll into balls and roll in 10x sugar.

title: baked french toast
directions: Place bread slices in greased baking dish.
Beat together eggs, milk, 1/3 cup sugar, lemon peel, vanilla, and salt.
Pour over bread; let stand for 5 minutes.
Turn over bread, cover and chill 5 hours to overnight.
Combine 1 tablespoon sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Sprinkle over bread.
Bake at 325° uncovered for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Bring sugar and vinegar to a boil and set aside.
Place cucumbers in a plastic bowl.
Stir in salt.
Let set 2 hours. Drain off water.
Add sugar and vinegar mixture.
Stir for 15 minutes occasionally.
Put in plastic boxes.
Freeze.

title: sausage con queso
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Melt cheese in crock-pot or heavy saucepan.
When cheese is melted, add drained sausage and Ro-Tel tomatoes; mix well.
Serve with tortillas chips and/or dip size corn chips.

title: the best chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray two 8-inch pans or 1 large pan. Mix the flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt in a bowl.
Pour in the water, oil, vanilla and vinegar and stir until well combined.
Add chocolate chips.
Pour into the prepared pans and bake 30 minutes or until done.
Cake can be iced or sprinkled with powdered sugar.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix the sugar, Swiss cheese and eggs in a bowl.
Pour into graham cracker pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Chill for 1 hour.
Top with your favorite topping.

title: pumpkin sundae pie
directions: Combine sugar, pumpkin, spice and salt.
Beat cream until stiff and fold into pumpkin mixture until no streaks of white show.
Spoon 1 1/2 pints ice cream into cooled 9-inch pie pan. Top with pumpkin cream mixture.
Refreeze until firm.
As you serve, use the remaining 1/2 pint ice cream for top of pie.

title: cheese salad
directions: Chop all ingredients and mix with mayonnaise.

title: easy barbecue pork ribs
directions: May add brown sugar and honey.

title: giant meatball sandwich
directions: Combine meats and shape into 1-inch balls.
Cook in large skillet over medium heat for 8 to 10 minutes.
Discard drippings. Add spaghetti sauce and garlic to skillet and cook 12 to 15 minutes.
Cut bread in half, top with meatballs and shredded cheese.

title: bill collins finger licking good barbecue sauce
directions: Combine and cook until onions are tender and sauce is thick. When cooking chicken, cook over low heat, turning and mopping chickens with the sauce about every 15 minutes.
Cook approximately 3 hours, or until wings and legs are ready to twist from the body.
Watch your heat and try not to burn the chickens. This recipe makes enough sauce for 6 chickens.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk.
Boil for exactly 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add last 4 ingredients; stir until stiff.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch or 8 x 8-inch buttered pan.

title: persimmon bars
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add egg and pulp.
Next add flour, spice and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased pan for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Pour glaze over cooled bars.

title: shannon's homemade rolls
directions: Mix water, oil, honey and yeast.
Let stand, covered, 15 minutes.
Add egg and mix well.
Add all flour and 1 1/4 cups bread flour; blend well.
Place remaining flour on waxed paper; knead 5 minutes.
Shape into rolls; place on cookie sheet.
Let rise 10 minutes.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Brush with melted butter.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt 3/4 stick margarine in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix flour, 3/4 cup sugar and milk.
Put this in pan with melted margarine.
Do not stir.
Then mix fruit, water and the other 1/2 cup sugar.
Add spice to taste.
Pour in pan with batter.
Do not stir.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: oven fried mozzarella sticks
directions: Cut Mozzarella cheese into eight 3 x 1/2 x 1/2-inch sticks. Set aside.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Scald milk and melt marshmallows in the hot milk, mix remaining ingredients and add to the milk and marshmallows.
Pack firmly in pan and put in cool place to age, 2 to 4 weeks.
Several times a week sprinkle with brandy or orange juices.
Other nuts may be used.
Keep cool forever.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Boil chicken in large pot, covered with water, along with salt to taste and the dried chiles.
When done, remove the chicken and use for another dish.
Remove chiles.
In skillet, saute tomatoes, garlic, onions and salt.
When tender, mash or place in blender and blend a little.
Add to chicken broth.
Cut the corn tortillas into very thin strips with scissors.
Fry until crisp and drain well.

title: baked bean trio
directions: Brown chopped onion and chopped green peppers.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 3 hours.

title: baked beans
directions: Drain pineapple.
Save 1/4 cup juice.
Combine pineapple juice, beans and the rest of ingredients, except bacon and sausage.
Place in baking dish.
Fry sausage and bacon halfway through.
Place in with beans and bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift together flour and sugar.
Cut in shortening.
Mix yeast with warm water until dissolved.
Add buttermilk to yeast.
Add mixture to flour.
Mix lightly until moistened.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 450° for about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, carrots and onions.
Cover with water and boil until tender.
Rub through a coarse sieve, saving the stock. Prepare a thin
white sauce with the butter, flour and milk;
add to
the
vegetable stock.
Reheat and season;
beat with a rotary beater.
Serve hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Melt cheese; mix with sour cream.
Add taco seasoning to meat mix.
Add tomatoes.
Mix well.

title: carrot ambrosia salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, tossing well.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: swiss steak(oven recipe)
directions: Cut meat into 4 pieces.
Trim fat.
Pound and brown in skillet.
Transfer meat to an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
In same skillet, combine undrained tomatoes, onion, celery, carrot and thyme.
Bring to boiling, scraping up any browned bits in pan. Pour over meat.
Cover and bake at 350° 1 hour or until tender. Serve over hot rice or noodles.
Serves 4.

title: avocado yogurt dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill several hours before serving.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk and pour into margarine.
Put apples on top.
Do not mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: easy oven fried chicken
directions: Line large cookie sheet with foil.
Pour vegetable oil into (cookie sheet) pan.
Coat each side of chicken in the oil.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Coat chicken with flour mixture on both sides and place back into lined cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until done.
Can increase all ingredients according to amount of chicken.

title: no names cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Bring to boil and boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix until peanut butter blends and add oatmeal.
Roll in balls and allow to dry.
Makes about 30 cookies.
Do not bake.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
With fingertips, crumble flour, brown sugar and butter into a coarse meal.
Peel and slice apples; mound into unbaked pie crust.
Sprinkle topping over apples.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour until brown and bubbly.

title: old fashioned creamy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk, baking chocolate, corn syrup and salt in a heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils.
Cook, stirring occasionally to 234° (or until forms a soft ball).
Remove from heat.
Add butter, vanilla and marshmallow, do not stir.
Allow to cool at room temperature without stirring until it reaches 110° or until fudge thickens and loses some of its gloss.
Quickly pour fudge into lightly buttered 8-inch square pan.
Makes about 1 1/2 pounds.

title: tempura
directions: Use on green peppers, cauliflower, sweet potatoes, mushrooms and onions.

title: pineapple cherry drop cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and beat.
Add soda dissolved in warm water.
Add flour in two siftings with salt. Add nuts and vanilla.
Stir well. Stir in pineapple last, stirring carefully so as not to dissolve pineapple. Drop by teaspoonful onto greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in oven at 350°, placing 1 piece of cut cherry on each cookie as it is placed on baking sheet.

title: lasagna roll-ups florentine
directions: Cook noodles until al dente.
Cool in cold water; dry and set aside.
Saute onion in 2 tablespoons butter until tender.
Combine spinach, onion, Mozzarella cheese, sour cream and egg; set aside.

title: brown bread with raisins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, sift together the dry ingredients.
In a small bowl, mix together the wet ingredients. Pour the wet mixture into the dry mixture, and combine with a fork.
Add the raisins.
Cut the dough in half and place each into 2 greased round cake pans.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pancakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and beat eggs until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients and beat until almost smooth.
Stir in milk and butter.
Beat only until mixture is smooth and free of lumps.

title: cheesy chive stuffed potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and rub skins with vegetable oil.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until done.
Allow potatoes to cool to touch.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Carefully scoop out pulp, leaving shells intact.
Coarsely chop pulp.

title: stripe-it-rich cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package, baking in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Remove from oven and poke holes at once down through the cake to the pan with round handle of wooden spoon.
Holes should be at 1-inch intervals.
After poking holes, combine pudding mix, sugar and eggs in saucepan.
Gradually stir in water; add butter.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to full boil.

title: hot pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple and pour into casserole dish.
Mix sugar and flour.
Sprinkle over pineapple.
Sprinkle 2 cups grated cheese over that.
Pour a little of the juice over that.
Crush 1 stick of Ritz crackers over that.
Slice 1 stick of butter over crackers.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: white decorator icing
directions: Cream butter and shortening together; add vanilla.
Cream half of powdered sugar.
Add the water, then cream rest of powdered sugar together.

title: easy cake
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Put crushed pineapple in pan. Add cherry pie filling.
Sprinkle cake mix over fruit.
Add nuts over this.
Slice oleo over cake in thin slices.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until nuts are brown.

title: chicken with wild rice
directions: Pour packet of rice and packet of seasoning into baking pan. Cut chicken into pieces, skin side up, on top of rice.
Combine soup and water and pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, in 375° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut stem and top from each pepper and remove core and seeds. Saute in skillet.
Add onions and cook until slightly brown.
Add ham and brown.
Stir in salt, paprika and rice.
Fill peppers with mixture.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lay chicken breasts flat; place 1 slice ham and Swiss cheese on top of chicken.
Fold in half and secure with a toothpick.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Let rise and then make into rolls.
Can be refrigerated for 1 week.
Butter tops before baking; start in warm oven.
Gradually turn to higher degree.
Bake slowly.

title: fruit ice
directions: Mash the bananas.
Add the pineapple juice.
Add the lemon juice.
Add the orange juice.
Mix all together and freeze.
Scoop what ice desired in drinks.

title: pepper mix for chicken and beef
directions: Mix and store in jar.
Use generously on meats.

title: spaghetti bake
directions: Fry bacon, onions and garlic.
Add meat and brown.
Stir in seasonings and tomato sauce with water.
Cover; simmer for 35 minutes.
Break 1/4 pound raw spaghetti into greased casserole. Cover with half of sauce and 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Repeat with 1/4 pound raw spaghetti, rest of sauce and rest of cheese.
Top with black olives.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375° until cheese melts golden brown.
Let stand 5 or 10 minutes before serving.
Makes a large casserole.

title: mustard sauce(sennepsaus)
directions: Melt butter; stir in dry ingredients and cook until it bubbles.
Add milk; cook on low heat about 10 minutes.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Melt Crisco and cool. Add sugar, molasses and egg.
Beat well with spoon.
Sift dry ingredients. Add to molasses mixture. Chill. Form into 1-inch balls and roll in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes on ungreased baking sheet.

title: madeira carrots
directions: Melt butter in saucepan. Add carrots, sugar, salt and wine. Cover and cook over medium heat for 6 to 8 minutes.
Lower heat and cook for an additional 10 minutes. Remove lid.
Sprinkle with tarragon and parsley.
Makes 6 servings. Delicious!

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl with fork, beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, corn syrup, butter and vanilla; stir until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 8 servings.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Combine milk, potatoes, shortening, sugar and salt in mixing bowl; let stand until lukewarm.
Add yeast softened in warm water and eggs.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour and beat well.
Cover and let stand in warm place until bubbly.
Add remaining flour and knead until smooth.
Place in greased bowl and put in refrigerator.

title: brunswick stew
directions: In large pot, cook hen and beef with water to cover until well done.
Remove meats.
Skin and debone hen.
Grind meats or use food processor.
Set meats aside.

title: deer roast
directions: Soak deer overnight in cold salty water.
Lay a long strip of foil in an iron skillet and lay 3 strips of bacon on foil. Place roast on bacon. Cut deep slits across roast.
Place a slice of onion in each slit.
Salt and pepper to taste. Wrap foil over roast and cook in a 350° oven for 3 hours or until tender.

title: bacon wrapped chicken breast
directions: Wash chicken breast; remove excess skin. Season with salt, pepper, garlic powder, and onion powder, to taste. (Tony's Chachere's Creole seasoning may be used.) Wrap strips of bacon around each breast, closing with a toothpick. Let set in refrigerator several hours for better flavor. Cook on grill until done. Chicken breasts tend to dry out so do not overcook. Enjoy!

title: barbecue hamburgers for 24 buns
directions: Mix ground
beef,
bread,
milk
and salt; form into 24 patties.
Brown
quickly on both sides.
Arrange in large pan. Make sauce of catsup, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, sugar and onions.
Pour
over
patties.
Cover
with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: apple brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Sift next 4 ingredients together, add remaining ingredients to creamed mixture.
Mix well, spread in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Cook cabbage leaves for 4 minutes in boiling salted water; drain.
Brown ground chuck; drain.
Mix meat with cooked brown rice, minced onion, salt, pepper and tomato sauce.
Divide meat into 12 portions, each portion placed in center of each cabbage leaf.
Roll and fold, seam side down in large baking dish.

title: candied yams
directions: Prepare and boil whole yams or sweet potatoes.
Drain.
Let cool.
Peel and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Arrange slices, overlapping, in a greased (Pam) casserole dish.
Dot with butter. Sprinkle lightly with salt.
Sprinkle evenly with brown sugar. Place small amount of low-sugar orange marmalade on top of slices.

title: chocolate punch bowl delight
directions: Mix pudding, milk, sour cream and 1/2 the the Cool Whip. Break cookies into pieces, crush candy bars.
Layer in punch bowl the cookies, pudding, candy-at least 2 layers.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle top with candy pieces and cherries.

title: chicken noodle supreme
directions: Put cooked noodles into greased casserole.
Add chicken.
Make paste of flour and butter.
Add broth and milk; thicken.
Add onion and soup.
Cook until blended.
Pour over noodles.
Sprinkle corn flakes and chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook cauliflower according to package directions or cook until tender if using fresh cauliflower. Drain; place in baking dish. Grate American cheese over top of cauliflower, then add White Sauce. Grate more cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Combine all ingredients together.

title: gone all day stew
directions: Mix together soup, water/wine and flour until smooth.
Combine with remaining ingredients in covered roaster.
Bake at 275° for 4 to 5 hours.
When ready to serve, adjust seasoning, if desired. Serve with crunchy French bread.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Pat hamburger in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Salt and pepper and cover with remaining ingredients.
Cook until cheese bubbles.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: white bread
directions: Scald milk; stir in sugar, salt and margarine.
Cool to lukewarm.
Measure warm water into a large bowl.
Sprinkle or crumble in yeast; stir until dissolved.
Add lukewarm milk mixture and 3 cups flour; beat until smooth.
Add enough additional flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out onto lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Form into a smooth ball.
Place in a greased bowl turning to grease top.
Cover; let rise in a warm place free from draft, until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour.

title: italian casserole
directions: *Small meatballs may be substituted for sausage or use both.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Combine sausage and onion in skillet.
Cook until meat it is brown and drain.
Add sauerkraut and 2 teaspoons bread crumbs. Combine cream cheese, parsley, mustard, dash of garlic salt and pepper.
Stir into sauerkraut mixture.
Chill and shape into balls and coat with flour.
Add milk to beaten egg.
Dip balls into egg mixture and roll into bread crumbs.
Fry in deep fat to brown, and then bake in 375 degree oven for 15-20 minutes.
Can be frozen after deep frying
and bake when needed.

title: chocolate coconut candies
directions: Combine potatoes, coconut, sugar and almond extract; mix well. Roll into 1-inch balls.
Refrigerate for 30 to 60 minutes.
If mixture is too soft to form balls, refrigerate first.
Mix chocolate chips, chocolate squares and wax; melt over hot water in double boiler.
Dip balls into chocolate coating.
Place in refrigerator to harden.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: killer dip
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain fat.
Mix sausage with cheese sauce; heat mix on medium heat until hot and serve with nachos.

title: meltaway sugar cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoon on ungreased pan.
Dip a glass in cinnamon sugar and press cookie.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hearty bacon potato chowder
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, cook bacon over medium heat for 5 minutes. Add potatoes and onion. Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until potatoes are tender (15 to 20 minutes).
Add remaining ingredients. Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until heated through (10 to 12 minutes).

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Partially fry chicken in oil until a light golden color. Remove from heat.
Prepare sauce, combining tomato sauce, paste, sugar and mushrooms.
Fry onion and pepper, sliced, until onion loses its color.
Add to sauce, along with oregano, garlic and Parmesan cheese.
Simmer 1/2 hour, seasoning to taste.
Place chicken in roasting pan.
Add sauce, covering chicken.
Add can of onions.
Cook 20 minutes at 375°.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on chicken and bake 10 more minutes.
Remove from oven; garnish with parsley.

title: french toast
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread together.
Slice bread 1-inch thick. Dip in batter.
Brown and spread with 1 teaspoon strawberry or pineapple cream cheese.
Keep warm in oven until ready to serve.
Yields 20 pieces.

title: ozark pudding
directions: Beat sugar into eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour into greased 8-inch pie pan.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for about 30 minutes.
Serve with cream or ice cream.

title: ham and scalloped potatoes
directions: Place slices of uncooked potatoes in layers in baking dish. Sprinkle each layer with flour, pepper and dot with butter.
If ham is salty, do not use additional salt.
Add milk in quantity sufficient to reach the surface of the sliced potatoes.
Place slice of ham on top and bake in preheated oven.

title: olive cheese puffs
directions: Blend cheese and other ingredients.
Squeeze juice out of olives using paper towels.
Cover olive with dough.
Freeze on cookie sheet.
Puffs must be frozen well.
Bake frozen puffs at 425° for 12 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: In a deep casserole dish put cabbage.
Break open wedges; then top with hamburger.
Slice onions on top of hamburger.
Add soups on top and cover.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: butter-pecan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream margarine and sugar; blend in egg.
Stir together with flour until creamy.
Chill 1 hour.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten in one direction with fork tines.
Top each with a pecan half.
Bake for 10 to 14 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 4 dozen.

title: salmon ball
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into a ball and chill.
Before serving, roll in nuts or parsley.
Serve with crackers or toast.

title: oatmeal pudding
directions: Combine oats, brown sugar, fruit, cinnamon and salt. Mix well. Combine milk, egg whites, oil and vanilla. Add to dry ingredients. Mix well. Bake in a preheated oven at 350° in a 9 inch pan for 50 to 100 minutes or until center is firm to the touch. Cool slightly. Serve with milk, yogurt and fruit, if desired. Store
left over pudding tightly covered in the refrigerator. Makes 8 servings.

title: dream bars
directions: Cream butter, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1 cup flour. Pat in an 8-inch square pan. Bake 10 minutes at 350°. Mix remaining ingredients well and pour over crust. Bake at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes. Cut while warm.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat sugar, flour and salt with eggs, until light in color. Add vanilla and milk; bake for 15 minutes at 450°, then 30 minutes at 325° in unbaked pie shell.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown beef, 1 onion and garlic.
Add tomato sauce, juice, green chili and spices.
In large greased pan, place a layer of chips, then cover with a layer of the meat mixture and 1 can beans.
Repeat and end with third layer of chips.
Bake in 350° oven, covered, for 45 minutes.
Then uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: holiday party punch
directions: Chill apple juice and ginger ale.
Mix just before serving and pour over ice cubes in punch bowl.
Garnish with lemon and lime slices, topped with green and red cherry quarters.
Makes 10 to 12 four-ounce servings.

title: german christmas cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, cinnamon, salt and melted chocolate.
Add the beaten egg and the mixture of baking soda and milk.
Stir in flour.
Roll thin and cut out with cookie cutters. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla; mix lightly.
Add dry ingredients; mix well, then beat in chopped nuts.
Pour into 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 20 minutes.
This bread freezes well.

title: microwave lasagna(easy, reasonably light and microwavable)
directions: Brown the ground turkey over medium heat.
Drain and combine with wine and spaghetti sauce.
Spread about 1/3 of meat sauce in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch glass dish, sprayed with cooking spray.
Place 4 uncooked noodles on top of the meat sauce. Layer one cup of cottage cheese and 3/4 cup of the Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat, using half of the remaining meat sauce, 4 uncooked noodles, 1 cup cottage cheese and 3/4 cup Mozzarella.
Top with remaining sauce. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Cover dish with plastic wrap, turning back one corner slightly to vent.
Microwave on Medium for 30 minutes, turning a quarter turn after 15 minutes. Uncover; add remaining 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese and microwave on Medium for an additional 2 minutes.
Re-cover and let stand for 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 generous servings.

title: blueberry smoothie pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In bowl, combine graham cracker crumbs, butter and lemon zest.
Press into a 9 1/2-inch pie plate and bake 12 minutes or until lightly browned; cool.
In large bowl, fold together yogurt and 3 cups whipped topping.
Fill crust with yogurt mixture; freeze 4 hours or overnight.
Top with remaining whipped topping and fruit.
Makes 8 servings.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: In a bowl, stir together blueberries, sugar, melted butter and lemon juice.
Place in an 8x8x2 inch baking dish.
Mix and sift dry ingredients; cut in shortening. Beat egg and milk together and stir into dry ingredients.
Spoon mixture over berry layer and spread gently to cover.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes or until browned.
Serve plain, with whipped cream or with ice cream.
8 servings.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix well. Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: pink dessert
directions: Mix all together with cottage cheese and jello. Add Cool Whip. Mix well. Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: hungarian pork and sauerkraut goulash
directions: Saute onion and garlic in small amount of oil.
Stir in dill weed and caraway seed.
Add boiling water, bouillon and pork cubes.
Mix in sauerkraut.
Simmer 1 to 2 hours until pork is tender.
(If desired, add 2 cups sour cream.)
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all above ingredients and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: david's favorite chili
directions: Brown ground chuck.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for at least 1 hour.

title: chili dip
directions: Mix and heat.
Keep warm while serving.

title: syrian baked chicken with lemon
directions: Preheat oven at 375° to 400°.
Dampen the chicken pieces and coat well with seasoned flour mixture.
Place chicken pieces in a baking pan that has been lightly coated with oil.
Dot each piece of chicken with a small pat of butter.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients.
Add the remaining ingredients.

title: honey drip chicken
directions: Place chicken on greased cookie sheet.
Mix honey and ketchup together.
Place lemon slices on chicken.
Brush with mixture every 15 minutes.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: butterscotch bars
directions: In a large mixing bowl, melt margarine in microwave.
Add brown sugar and vanilla.
Allow to cool; then add eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients and stir into margarine-sugar mixture. Add pecans.
Pour into a greased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Spread evenly. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: gingered carrots
directions: Peel carrots and cut into julienne strips.
Fill a saucepan with water.
Add carrots, bring to a boil and cook 5 to 6 minutes, until tender.
Drain and dry completely on paper towels. In a separate saucepan melt butter. Add sugar and ginger.
Add carrots, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring, over low heat for 3 to 4 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli with salt and onion; drain well.
Add mayonnaise, cheese and mushroom soup; mix.
Add pecans; mix.
Add eggs; mix well.
Put in greased dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken italian
directions: Wash chicken; remove excess fat.
Dip chicken in eggs and then in breadcrumbs.
Brown lightly in oil.
Arrange browned chicken in baking dish.
Sprinkle half the Mozzarella cheese and half the Parmesan cheese over it.
Pour the spaghetti sauce over chicken and cheese.
Top with remaining cheese and bake at 350° (uncovered) for 30 minutes.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix cake mix by directions on box.
Layer pecans and coconut in a greased pan.
Then pour cake mixture on top.

title: curried beef salad
directions: Cut beef into 1 1/2 x 3/4-inch pieces.
In large bowl, combine beef, apples, peaches, celery and onions.
Mix lightly.
In small bowl, mix mayonnaise, sour cream and curry powder until well blended.
Add to beef mixture; toss to coat.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour or until well chilled.
To serve, arrange lettuce on platter.
Spoon beef salad on top.
Yields 4 servings, per serving about 305 calories, 9 g fat.

title: pecan delights
directions: Let shortening and sugar soften in a bowl at room temperature, then mix with mixer, adding all other ingredients, except nuts. Stir in nuts with a spoon.
Drop in amounts of about 1 teaspoon on baking sheet.
Bake at 300° for 1/2 hour (just until edges begin to turn brown).
Remove from baking sheet while hot and place on paper towels.
Let cool.
It is important to put cookies on paper towel.
Makes 60 to 75 cookies.
These cookies freeze well.

title: kabob marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients together and marinade beef kabobs, steak or chicken.

title: lasagna
directions: Mix and brown first 8 ingredients.
Add sauce to meat mixture. Boil lasagna noodles until tender, then layer noodles, meat mix, Mozzarella cheese, cottage cheese, Cheddar cheese and Parmesan cheese (should make 2 or 3 layers).
On last layer, top with more Cheddar cheese.
Should make 2 pans of lasagna.
Freeze one for later.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix together good and put in an unbaked pie shell.
Cook until knife slipped in pie comes out clean.

title: cheesy tarts
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cut up the stick of butter and rub the butter into the flour until it is crumbly. In another bowl mix the cottage cheese and honey.
Add this second mixture to the first.
Mix with hands until smooth.
Flour the table top or a board and sprinkle some more flour on the dough. Roll out until thin like a pie crust.
Cut dough into circles. Place on cookie sheet or tart pans.
Spread a little jam in the middle.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool and eat.

title: cherry crumble
directions: Pour cherry pie filling in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Crumble up and spread evenly on top of cherries the pound cake mix.
Pour melted margarine evenly over dry cake mix.
Gently spread and mix margarine with cake mix without mixing cherries. Cook in oven at 350° for 45 minutes or until cake mixture is golden brown.

title: chicken wings
directions: Cut off end of wing and discard.
(I make chicken broth with them.)
Marinate overnight in sauce made from above ingredients. Bake, uncovered, for about 1 hour.

title: idaho potato chili
directions: Heat oil in large saucepan over medium -high heat.
Add onions, pepper and garlic.
Cook and stir 5 minutes or until softened.
Add Turkey.
Cook and stir 5 to 6 minutes or until no longer pink, breaking up with a spoon.
Stir in chili powder.
Cook for 1 minute.
Add canned tomatoes, potatoes, beans, 1 cup water and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Simmer, covered, 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cilantro.
Top with yogurt and green onion.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: italian coconut cream cake
directions: Beat the sugar, 5 egg yolks and butter together.
Add flour, baking soda, milk, coconut, pecans and vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to boil and stir until sugar and jello are dissolved.
Take off heat and add cream cheese, cut in small pieces.
Stir until cheese melts; cool.
Add container of whipped topping.
Put in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: nana's lazy lasagna
directions: Saute hamburg, clove of garlic and 2 teaspoons of chopped onion.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Cook noodles al dente.
Cook and drain chopped spinach.
Mix first 7 ingredients in a large bowl. Cover bottom of baking dish with sauce.
Layer half the noodle mixture, then the sauce.
Repeat the layering.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot. Serves 6.

title: italian sausage soup
directions: Cook sausage, then saute the onion and green peppers.
Add broth and red wine; bring to a boil.
Add garlic, basil, oregano, parsley and tomatoes.
Cover and cook for 1 hour.
Slow to simmer. Serve over cooked pasta noodles.
Add Parmesan cheese to bowl. Serve with garlic bread.

title: happy home recipe
directions: Combine Love and Loyalty.
Mix thoroughly with Faith.
Blend with Tenderness, Kindness, Understanding and Forgiveness.
Add Friendship and Hope.
Sprinkle abundantly with Laughter.
Bake with plenty of Sunshine.
Serve daily with smiles.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Mix flour, 1 1/2 cups sugar, baking powder and salt in bowl. Make a well in center and add oil, egg yolks, water, coconut and orange rind.
Beat until smooth.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff peaks form.
Gradually pour egg yolk mixture over egg whites, folding gently just until blended (do not beat or stir).

title: strawberry-banana lush mush punch
directions: Cook sugar and water until melts.
Cool and add pineapple juice, orange juice, water and lemon juice.
Freeze in 1/2 gallon or 1 gallon containers.
Thaw to slush (2 to 3 hours) before using.
Add bananas, strawberries, 7-up or ginger ale and red food coloring.
Mix well and serve immediately to 50 people.
Enjoy!!!

title: biscuits
directions: Blend flour and shortening with fork or pastry blender.
Blend in baking powder and salt. Add enough milk for stiff dough. Pat out on floured board.
Cut out with biscuit cutter.
Place in greased pan, turning over each biscuit.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour cornish hens
directions: *Do not stack if you make more.

title: frozen almond punch
directions: Bring 4 cups sugar, 2 large lemon jello, and 4 cups water to a boil; cool and add pineapple juice, frozen orange juice, lemon juice, almond flavoring, and 1 gallon cold water.
Mix and freeze and take out 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: jalapeno cheese cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into an 8 x 12-inch (approximate) baking dish.
Bake at 425° about 25 minutes or until done.

title: microwave pralines
directions: In 3-quart microwavable bowl, stir first 5 ingredients. Cover and vent.
Microwave on high for 8 minutes, stirring after 4 minutes.
Stir in pecans and vanilla.
Cook on high, covered, for 2 minutes.
Stir in powdered sugar until thick and not glossy. Quickly drop by spoonfuls onto buttered waxed paper.
If mixture becomes thick, stir in a few drops of hot water.
Makes 20.

title: spoon bread
directions: Combine ingredients in order and pour into 10-inch buttered casserole dish.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, salt and cornstarch in saucepan.
Blend in milk.
Cook over medium heat; stir constantly, until thickened. Cook 2 to 3 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Pour into individual cups or serving bowl.
Chill.

title: miniature pizza pockets
directions: Brown sausage in a skillet over moderately high heat; drain and discard fat.
Add mushrooms and onion and cook, stirring, until tender.
Remove from heat and stir in pizza sauce, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses.
Set aside to cool.
Thaw pastry 20 minutes; unfold.
On lightly floured surface, roll each sheet to a 12-inch square; cut each into sixteen 3-inch squares.
Top each square with some of the sausage mixture.
Brush edges of pastry with egg mixture; fold in half to form triangles.
Press edges together with the tines of a fork.
Brush with more egg; transfer to ungreased baking sheets and bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sweet sour cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage in a small amount of salted water until crisp-tender.
Switch off heat.
Do not drain.
In a small saute pan, saute onion in oil until lightly brown.

Add brown sugar, vinegar and about 1/2 cup of the cooking juice from the cabbage. Taste the sauce and add salt and pepper or more brown sugar or vinegar, according to how much sweetness or tartness you like. Drain the cabbage and pour sauce over the cabbage, making sure all the surface is coated with the sauce.
Serve immediately.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Season spareribs with salt, pepper, garlic powder and soul seasoning if used.
Mix brown sugar and vinegar and rub on meat generously.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Turn once.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Boil egg
yolks,
sugar,
salt,
cream	or
milk, lemon juice, pineapple
juice
and cornstarch until thick.
Add Cool Whip, marshmallows,
pineapple and nuts (if desired).
Can add any other fruit you like.
Mix well and let stand overnight.

title: crescent delight
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick spray.
Layer one can of crescent rolls on bottom.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and egg yolk together.
Pour in pan.
Layer the second can of rolls on cheese mixture.
Beat egg white; pour on top.
Sprinkle cinnamon-sugar on top of all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: "gukes" sandwich
directions: Mix meat, mustard, ketchup and seasoning.
Spread on half of bun.
Put in broiler pan and cook until done.
Top with cheese slice.

title: vegetable marinade
directions: Marinate mixture of cherry tomatoes, black olives, celery, carrots, cauliflower and green peppers.

title: bananas foster
directions: In a small bowl, combine brown sugar and cinnamon with a fork, set aside.
In a heavy 12-inch skillet, melt margarine over medium heat.
Add cinnamon-sugar mixture, stir until sugar melts.
Pour in banana liqueur and 1/4 cup rum.
Cook, stirring, until syrupy and thick (about 5 minutes).
Add bananas, lightly coating with syrup.
Add remaining 1/4 cup rum, swirl pan, ignite rum.
Quickly swirl pan, cook, basting bananas with sauce until flame goes out. Remove from heat.
Place 2 banana slices on each of 4 plates, side by side.
Place
scoop of ice cream on top of each serving. Drizzle with sauce.
Decorate with mint, if desired.
Serve immediately.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Cook the first 7 ingredients until vegetables are tender, then add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Makes 16 to 20 servings.

title: cream puffs(eclairs)
directions: Heat to boiling:
water, butter and salt.
Add flour and eggs. Place on cookie sheet to desired size.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
Split and bake 10 minutes longer.
Cool and fill halves with 2 packages vanilla pudding (prepared as package directs). Cover with top halves and coat with chocolate and 10x sugar.

title: bride's pink punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Dissolve Kool-Aid in cold water.
Add sugar.
Stir well.
Add pineapple juice and Jell-O. Refrigerate.
Add 7-Up and sherbet just before serving.
Makes 35 servings.

title: pineapple cake - shirleys' cake
directions: Combine
and
beat
until blended.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan about 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cherry squares
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour; spread in large cookie sheet.
Drop pie filling by spoonful on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon bars
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar, add flour and salt.
Pat firmly into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie(from home grown pumpkins)
directions: Combine beaten eggs, sugar, flour, salt and spices.
Add pumpkin; mix and stir in milk.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Put shortening in pan and set in oven to melt.
Mix flour, salt and pepper in paper bag.
Shake 3 or 4 pieces of chicken at a time in bag and coat.
Place chicken, skin side down in a single layer in hot shortening.
Bake 30 minutes, then turn and bake another 30 minutes until tender.
Also good for pork chops.

title: frozen banana salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Freeze.
Let stand at room temperature 20 minutes before serving.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve sugar, butter and salt in boiling water.
Let cool until lukewarm, then add yeast which has been dissolved in 2 tablespoons warm water.
Add eggs, beaten well, then add flour. Mix well.
Cover with wax paper and set in refrigerator overnight.

title: salmon party log
directions: Drain, clean and flake salmon.
Combine all ingredients except pecans and parsley.
Chill in refrigerator for several hours. Roll into log and let set in refrigerator until the next day, then roll into mixture of chopped pecans and parsley.

title: oh, my darling sugar cookies(author: janet culver)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: super salad
directions: Slice the broccoli, green onions, cauliflower and mushrooms. Cut cherry tomatoes in half and add to broccoli mixture.
Pour dressing over all and marinate overnight.

title: fruit cocktail with yogurt or sour cream
directions: Into 4 serving glasses, distribute strawberries.
Cover with 2 teaspoons yogurt or sour cream in each glass.
Next, place a layer of pineapple, a layer of bananas, then another layer of yogurt. Top off with a large strawberry.
Serves 4. (Each serving contains 164 calories.)

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top or cornflake crumbs.

title: cabbage and noodles
directions: Cook cabbage, onions, celery and apple together.
Cook noodles separately in pan according to package directions until done.
Mix all together with salt, pepper and oleo to taste.

title: mormon muffins
directions: Add soda to hot water and let cool.
Whip shortening and sugar until light and fluffy; add eggs slowly.
Mix well; add buttermilk, flour and salt; mix well, then add soda water very slowly.
Fold the 2 Bran cereals to the mixture; slowly add nuts. Spoon into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 18 minutes; let cool for 5 minutes.

title: banana raisin cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; beat in egg.
Add mashed bananas, oats, raisins and nuts.
Add salt to flour, then add soda.
Add to creamed mixture.
Drop by tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: squirrel sauce piquant
directions: Cut up meat; salt and pepper.
Brown until tender in pot with 1/8 inch oil.
Add small amounts water from time to time to prevent sticking.
Remove meat when tender.

title: 7-layer casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place ingredients in order in a 2-quart baking dish with a tight fitting lid.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer, until bacon is crisp. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mashed potatoes with ground beef
directions: Boil potatoes until done; mash, then add salt, pepper and milk.
Divide into two halves.
Saute onion in oil until golden brown; add ground beef, salt, pepper and allspice.
Cook until done.
Grease pan; add 1/2 the bread crumbs and put half the mashed potatoes.
Spread evenly.
Add meat in middle of spread. Add the second half of potatoes; spread evenly.
Add some milk on top of potatoes; sprinkle 1/2 of bread crumbs.
Add little oil on top.
Bake at 400° for 1/2 hour or until golden brown on top. Makes enough for 6 people.

title: wendy's chili
directions: Brown hamburger.
Put soup in blender, then pour over browning meat.
Cook about 5 minutes and add the rest of the ingredients. Simmer.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine mixed vegetables, onions, celery, water chestnuts, water, salt and pepper.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir; cook 4 more minutes.
Drain well.
Add mayonnaise and cheese. Crumble crackers; mix with melted oleo and spread on top.
Cook until golden brown at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients in a saucepan until mixture forms soft ball in cold water.
Beat in the remaining ingredients. Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool completely and cut into squares.
Makes about 2 1/2 to 3 dozen pieces of candy.

title: hard (or vienna) rolls
directions: Sift flour. Dissolve 1 package yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm water. Combine 1 cup water, sugar, salt, melted shortening and the dissolved yeast mixture. Lightly fold in beaten egg whites.
