Add enough of the sifted flour to make a soft dough. Knead the dough for about 10 minutes until it becomes smooth and elastic. Allow the dough to rise twice. After the second rising, punch down and knead for about 1 minute, then let rest, covered, for about 10 minutes before shaping into 12 oblong (or round) pieces. Place them about 3-inches apart on a greased baking sheet.

title: spanish scalloped potatoes
directions: Place potatoes, onions and margarine in electric skillet. Saute or lightly brown, then add tomato and spices to taste. Add tomato sauce and water and simmer.
When potatoes are done, sprinkle grated cheese over top.
Cover until cheese is melted and serve.

title: upside-down bacon corn cake
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Mix egg and milk and add.
Stir in fat.
Pour boiling water over the bacon; drain and dry. Arrange bacon strips in bottoms of 2 (8-inch) round cake pans. Pour half the batter into each.
Bake in a hot oven (425°) for about 25 minutes.

title: baked swordfish
directions: Arrange pieces of swordfish in a baking dish. Pour milk into dish, not covering fish. Put buttered breadcrumbs on top and bake at 350° until done.

title: slumgullion-on-a-bun
directions: Shape ground meat into large patty in a kettle or Dutch oven. Brown 5 minutes on each side, then break up into chunks.
Add onion and garlic; saute until soft.
Add all ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Toast hamburger buns; put slumgullion over bun. Serves about 6 to 8.

title: tangerine cream pie
directions: Combine Egg Beaters, sugar, cinnamon, cornstarch (mix with small amount of milk), nutmeg, milk and salt.
Cook over medium fire until thick.
Place tangerine slices, drained, over bottom of cooked pie shell.
Peak over pie.
Cook until egg whites are golden brown at 350°.
Cool and serve.

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix and put in greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Do not overbake.

title: mississippi mud fool's fudge
directions: Mix well cracker crumbs, peanut butter and sugar; add margarine, mixing thoroughly.
Firmly press mixture into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips in top of a double boiler. Pour melted chocolate over peanut butter.
Let cool at room temperature before slicing into squares.

title: burrito
directions: Brown the hamburger, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix tomato juice and taco mix; add to hamburger mixture.
Place filling down the center of a flour tortilla and sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.
Roll up and place seam on bottom.
Cover with foil and heat in oven at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: turkey-noodle casserole
directions: Chop turkey into bite-sized pieces.
Shred about 1/2 package of chipped beef (use to taste).
Chop onion.
Add these ingredients to cooked and drained noodles.
Mix well.
In a bowl, dilute chicken soup with one soup can of broth.
Stir in sour cream, milk, salt and pepper.
Combine with noodle mixture and pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with paprika and Cheddar cheese as desired.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes, uncovered, or until golden.

title: herb butter zucchini fans
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a small bowl and set aside. Cut each zucchini into lengthwise slices, leaving slices attached at stem end.
Fan slices out and spread evenly with butter mixture.
Place in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan; add water. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Combine cheese and breadcrumbs; sprinkle on zucchini and broil 4 inches from heat 2 minutes or until cheese melts.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: frozen pineapple-cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze.
If desired, may add red food coloring.
Use an oblong dish.
Serves 10.

title: sausage-squash casserole
directions: Mix squash and sausage.
Add sour cream and onion, bread crumbs and grated cheese.
Top with Durkee onions.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: susan's salmon casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine Ritz crackers, oleo, garlic powder, Mrs. Dash, onion powder, salt and pepper.
Spray Pam in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour 1/2 Ritz cracker combination into bottom of casserole.
Add drained, flaked salmon.
Cover with remaining crackers.
Add milk over top of casserole.
Bake 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: gourmet pork chops
directions: Coat chops with mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Brown on both sides in shortening.
Place in baking pan.
Combine soup, 3/4 cup of water, ginger and rosemary and pour over chops.
Sprinkle with half the onions.
Cover and bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until meat is tender.
Uncover and sprinkle with remaining onions and bake for 10 minutes.
Remove meat; blend sour cream into sauce. Heat and use this for gravy.
Good served with rice or noodles.

title: chili con carne with chili sauce
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then simmer gently for 30 minutes.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: coconut oatmeal delights
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add milk and eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: barbecued meat balls
directions: Mix well; form into 2-inch patties.
Brown in shortening.

title: party chicken
directions: Wrap chicken breasts with bacon and chipped beef. Place in greased baking dish.
Mix soup, sour cream and cooking sherry. Pour over chicken.
Refrigerate for a few hours.
Bake uncovered in 275° oven for 3 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into buttered baking dish. Cover with crushed Cheez-Its.
Bake at 350° to 400° about 20 minutes.

title: special noodle casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper with meat and brown.
Add tomato sauce, sugar, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Cook 15 minutes. Mix green onions with cheese and sour cream, using a mixer.
Layer the cooked noodles and cheese mixture, then top with the tomato sauce mixture.
Put grated cheese on top and bake until cheese melts and casserole is hot.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time and continue mixing until light.
Measure dry ingredients into a small mixing bowl and mix together.
Combine 2 teaspoons cinnamon and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Roll dough into balls.
Roll balls in cinnamon.
Place on greased pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: one basic dough, six different cookies
directions: Mix up basic dough; it's scrumptious.
Roll out and cut into shapes to make Vanilla Sugar Cookies.
Before baking, decorate with cinnamon hearts, jimmies and gumdrops.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake until done at 350°.

title: buttermilk egg custard
directions: Beat egg yolk; add buttermilk, sugar and butter.
Mix well before putting in flour.
Add 2 teaspoons sweet milk.
Add lemon flavor.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: deluxe pecan pie
directions: Melt butter.
Mix in sugar and syrup, then add eggs and vanilla.
Add pecans.
Put in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: quick and easy lasagna
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Add tomato sauce and season to taste with salt and pepper.
Cook egg noodles according to directions. Mix 3/4 of sour cream and 3/4 of cream cheese until smooth.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Mix salt and pepper with flour; roll strips of beef in mixture, brown in fat and remove from skillet.
Add beef stock, tomato juice, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to a boil; add meat.
Simmer, covered, until meat is almost tender.
Add sour cream and continue simmering, uncovered, until meat is tender. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on the box.
Bake two cake layers.
While
the layers are cooling, prepare the pudding as directed on the box.
Put one layer of cake in the bottom of a trifle dish.
Top
cake
with the vanilla pudding.
Put 2/3 of the strawberries
on top of the pudding.
Add the 2nd layer of cake. Put
the
Cool
Whip
on top of the cake.
Top the Cool Whip with the remaining strawberries.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a pan greased with butter. Bake at 325° until golden brown.

title: rice krispie balls
directions: Put mixture in saucepan over low heat and bring to a boil. Remove from heat and add Rice Krispies and vanilla.
Form into balls and roll in flaked coconut.
Refrigerate cookies.

title: lemon delight
directions: Cut butter into flour until mixture resembles coarse meal; stir 1/2 cup pecans into flour mixture.
Press pecan mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: jeanie's potatoes
directions: Mix cheese, onion, sour cream and soup.
Mix potatoes with cheese mixture and put in casserole dish.
Sprinkle crushed corn flakes over the top.
Put melted butter over corn flakes and bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: pralines
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients over slow fire until sugar melts. Add pecans and boil 3 to 5 minutes.
Beat until creamy.
Drop on waxed paper from teaspoon and cool.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Cook spinach according to microwave directions.
Drain.
Cut cheese in chunks.
Combine with the rest of the ingredients. Stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir once during the baking time. Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: betty's chicken casserole
directions: Crush the entire package of crackers and mix with melted margarine.
Press half of this mixture in a 1-quart casserole dish. Mix the remaining ingredients together and pour over cracker mixture in casserole.
Place remaining cracker mixture over this and bake at 375° for about 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 5-quart casserole.
Cook, covered, at 250°
for 5 hours.
After 3 1/2 hours of cooking, stir well; continue cooking.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine vegetables, mushroom soup, mayonnaise and onion.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish, top with crumbled crackers.
Bake at 350° for 20 or 30 minutes or until casserole is bubbly and brown.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add beaten eggs and syrup.
Mix well. Add pecans.
Fold in pecans.
Pour into 9-inch baked pie shell. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: Melt butter or margarine in large skillet over medium heat; add mushrooms and onion and saute until tender, about 5 to 7 minutes. Sprinkle flour, salt, pepper and nutmeg over vegetables; stir to blend well. Place in 5-quart slow cooker. Using wire whisk, beat in water, cream or half-and-half, sour cream and chicken broth. Cook covered, on LOW for 4 hours. Turn setting to HIGH; cook 1 hour longer, stirring occasionally. Stir in parsley and serve.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° until firm (30 to 40 minutes).

title: cornmeal cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar in large bowl.
Add egg and beat well. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop dough from spoon onto greased baking pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes or until lightly brown.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: crostata(italian apple tart)
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, stir together flour, sugar and baking powder.
Cut in margarine or butter until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
In another mixing bowl, beat egg slightly with a fork; stir in milk and vanilla.
Add milk mixture to flour mixture; mix well.

title: german potato soup
directions: Peel potatoes and dice into 1/2 to 1-inch cubes. Dice bacon and chop onion. Fry bacon and onion until crisp.
Drain off grease. Bring water and bouillon to a boil. Add potatoes, bacon and onion. Cook until the potatoes are done. Serve with breadsticks or crescent rolls.
(I like to mash the potatoes once they are in my bowl.)

title: banana cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box, making two layers.
Let cool. Mash bananas and put 1/2 between the two layers and remaining 1/2 on top.
Top with Cool Whip.
Best if able to set in refrigerator overnight.
This cake also can be frozen and used at a later date.

title: one dish chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender.
Cook rice.
Put into bottom of casserole dish.
Place chicken over rice.
Cover with choice of soup.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° until soup has baked into chicken and rice.
Punch holes in foil for steam to escape.
Cool a few minutes.

title: mac and cheese casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes a 2-quart casserole.

title: greek cracker spread
directions: Make salad dressing according to directions.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: batter for fried shrimp
directions: Prepare the batter with wire whisk.
Wash shrimp and devein. Immerse shrimp in batter and drop into heated oil.
Turning them with a slotted spoon, deep fry about 2 to 3 minutes, until golden. Transfer shrimp to paper towels to drain.

title: turkey divan
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions. Drain well. Arrange broccoli in a single layer in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Top with turkey.
Combine soup and milk. Stir well.
Pour soup mixture over turkey. Arrange cheese slices over casserole. Sprinkle with onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream eggs, sugar and shortening until smooth.
Add mashed bananas.
Mix together dry ingredients and add alternately with sour milk and vanilla.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° in a 13 x 9-inch pan for about 45 minutes.
Bake cupcakes for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box but use milk instead of water.
Bake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bring to boil crushed pineapple and sugar.
When cake is done, punch holes in it and pour pineapple mixture over cake.
Let set for a while.

title: apple turnovers
directions: Press two biscuits together and roll them out thin as you can. Spread 1/4 stick butter on baking pan.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Put 3 tablespoons fried apples on one half of the biscuits, fold the other half over the apples and press the other side down, using a fork.
Put in oven and bake 20 to 25 minutes.
When the bottom of the turnovers are brown, brush with butter on top and turn them over and bake until brown.

title: chocolate swirl cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine chocolate chips and 1/2 cup sugar in medium bowl.
Microwave until chips melt and mixture is smooth.
Set aside.
Combine crumbs, 2 tablespoons sugar and butter in a small bowl; mix well.
Pat firmly into a 9-inch spring-form pan, covering bottom and 1 inch up sides.

title: coke salad
directions: Drain juice from cherries and pineapple into saucepan and heat to boiling.
Add jello, both flavors, and stir until dissolved. Add Coca-Cola.
Chill until starts to gel.
Add all of fruit and cup of pecans.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook on High for 3 1/2 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Place ground beef in 2 quart casserole. Cover and microwave on High 6 to 8 minutes.
Stir halfway through cooking.
Drain all grease.
Add tomato sauce, paste, water, soup mix, seasonings and sugar.
Cover and microwave on High 6 to 8 minutes. Stir halfway through cooking.
Microwave on Low (30%) for 10 minutes to blend flavors.
Cook noodles according to directions.
Rinse noodles in cold water.
Place alternate layers of noodles, cottage cheese, sauce and Mozzarella in large ceramic or Corning Ware dish, ending with sauce. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes or microwave on High for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.

title: pineapple salad(good for diabetics)
directions: Add boiling water to gelatin dessert.
Stir until dissolved. Add pineapple juice and Sprite.
Chill until medium stiff.
Whip with mixer until foamy.
Gradually whip the whipped topping into the jello mixture.
Fold in pineapple.
Pour into mold.
Chill until set.

title: pecan bars a la wolverines
directions: Combine flour and sugar and cut in butter until like coarse bread crumbs.
Stir in pecans.
Press this crust into bottom of a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Top with chopped nuts. Store in refrigerator.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Put yeast
in
lukewarm
water;
scald milk.
Add sugar, salt and shortening;
cool to lukewarm.
Add 2 cups flour; beat well. Add eggs and yeast to milk and blend well; add remaining flour to make
soft
dough.
Turn
out on lightly floured board and knead. Shape rolls in greased baking pans.
Brush top with butter.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double in bulk, 1 to 2 hours. Bake
in
hot
oven
for 12 to 15 minutes. This makes good cinnamon rolls.

title: black beans cuban style
directions: Soak beans in water overnight.
Add salt and cook beans until soft.
In a mortar, mash the garlic; add to it the cumin, oregano and vinegar.

title: tossed strawberry salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together and serve with poppy seed dressing.

title: italian chicken scampi
directions: Rinse chicken and cut into 1-inch strips.
Combine oil, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, cheese, parsley flakes, oregano, garlic powder, salt and pepper in bowl.
Mix well.
Let marinate in refrigerator a couple hours or overnight.
Drain, reserving marinade.
Place chicken in shallow pan.
Broil 8 inches from heat until cooked thoroughly, turning once.
Heat reserved marinade to serving temperature in saucepan.
Pour over chicken in serving dish.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: funnel cake
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add egg and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Pour batter into hot oil and fry until golden, turning only once.
Drain.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients.
Pour into small casserole dish.
Slice eggs on top.
Pour cream of mushroom soup on top. Sprinkle lightly with bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: 5-cup fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit; mix together.
Add sour cream; mix well.
Add pecans and coconut; mix in, then add marshmallows.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.
Serve cold.

title: carolyn's meringue drops
directions: Preheat oven to 200°.
Line 2 large cookie sheets with foil. In small bowl with mixer at high speed beat egg whites, cream of tartar and salt until soft peaks form.
Beating at high speed gradually beat in sugar 2 tablespoons at a time, beating well after each addition until sugar is completely dissolved.
Add vanilla and continue beating at high speed until meringue stands stiff.
Spoon meringue into decorating bag using medium writing tip.
For each cookie pipe some meringue onto foil in a continuous upward spiral and 1-inch high.
Space cookies about 1-inch apart. Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool cookie sheets on wire rack. Remove carefully.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add peaches. Combine remainder of ingredients in bowl. Add to pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar in saucepan.
Stir in milk.
Add margarine.
Place on moderate heat and stir until it reaches a full boil.
Boil 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until well blended.
Spoon onto wax paper. Let cool.

title: spice buns
directions: Place salt, sugar, flour
and
spices
in
sieve; sift. Stir soda into milk and add.
Add
molasses and lard.
Add egg last. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 18 buns.

title: toffee cookies
directions: Oil a cookie sheet.
Line with foil.
Oil the foil.
Line with graham crackers.
Melt margarine and add brown sugar.
Let boil for 2 minutes.
Pour over graham crackers.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Spread.
Add pecans on top.
Refrigerate until completely cooled.
Peel the foil off and break into pieces.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Bring to boil butter, brown sugar, salt and Karo; boil 5 minutes (stirring constantly!).
Take off heat and add soda and vanilla.
Pour over popcorn and nuts which you have in large, shallow pan.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Bake the cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan or dish, as directed.
When cake is done, poke holes in cake across top.
Pour sweetened condensed milk on top and spread butterscotch topping over it. Chill cake.
Spread whipped topping on top of cake and sprinkle crushed Butterfingers over top of whipped topping.

title: chocolate dip
directions: Melt over hot water, dip and place on wax paper.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Put sugar, milk, butter and cocoa in a saucepan.
Bring to a full boil.
Cook 1 minute (slightly more in humid weather), stirring often.
Add vanilla.
Pour over oats and peanut butter quickly.
Stir well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.
Let stand 30 minutes.
If they won't harden they can be refrigerated and served cold.

title: reuben casserole(good for st. patrick's day or new year's party)
directions: Butter a casserole dish, then place corned beef (regular or low-fat) in bottom of dish.
Add sauerkraut, Swiss cheese, Thousand Island dressing, cubes of rye bread and butter or margarine.
Place sauerkraut on top of beef; spread with Thousand Island dressing. Soak rye bread cubes in butter and sprinkle over top.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with a salad.

title: "nanny's great chocolate pie"
directions: Heat 1 cup milk and butter in pot.
Dissolve sugar, cocoa, salt and cornstarch in the remaining 1/2 cup of milk.
Add well beaten egg yolks.
Pour this mixture into hot milk and butter. Cook until stiff, stirring constantly.
Put cocoa in baked pie shell.

title: never fail custard pie
directions: Scald milk.
Beat eggs; add sugar and vanilla.
Add to milk. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Top with nutmeg and cinnamon.
Bake at 415° for 20 minutes.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour in 2 unbaked pie shells (small ones).
Bake at 350° about	45
to 50 minutes, or until done.

title: pineapple mint mold
directions: Drain pineapple; keep syrup and place in saucepan.
Soften gelatin in syrup.
Add jelly and dash of salt.
Heat and stir until all dissolved and jelly melted.
Stir in pineapple; chill until mixture is thickened and syrupy.
Whip cream with sugar until stiff; fold into mixture.
Spoon into mold and freeze.
Let stand at room temperature 15 minutes before serving.

title: hot spiced apple cider
directions: Combine ingredients in a large saucepan.
Heat slowly until boiling.
Boil 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove spices.
Serve hot.

title: peanut crunch pie
directions: Reserve some chopped peanut brittle for decoration.
Mix remaining brittle with the ice cream in large bowl.
Spoon into crust mounding it in center.
Smooth with metal spatula; cover with foil and freeze at least 6 hours or overnight.
Stir chocolate chips and heavy cream in bowl and microwave on Low until chocolate melts and mix is smooth.
Stir in powdered sugar and peanut butter until blended.
Put pie on waxed paper to catch drips.
Pour chocolate mix over pie, spreading it quickly with a thin metal spatula.
Freeze 1 hour or until topping is firm.
Just before serving, top with remaining brittle.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease an 8x8x2 inch baking pan.
Sift flour with sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add corn meal, mixing well.
Set aside.
In medium bowl, combine egg, salad oil and milk, mixing well.
Add flour mixture, stirring only until flour mixture is moistened.
Spoon batter into prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: five cup salad
directions: Drain juice from fruit and mix all together long enough before serving to chill well.

title: easy mexican pizzas
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place 5 tortillas on greased baking sheets.
Sprinkle each with 1/4 cup cheese.
Place remaining tortillas on top of cheese.
Heat vegetable oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken, onions and green peppers.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Add 2 tablespoons taco seasoning mix and 1 tablespoon water; mix well. Remove from heat.
Combine refried beans, remaining seasoning mix and 1 tablespoon of water in small bowl.
Heat in microwave until warm.
Spread about 1/4 cup bean mixture on each tortilla.
Layer with a drizzle of taco sauce, chicken mixture, remaining cheese and toppings.
Bake for 5 to 8 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: new england clam soup
directions: Chop clams coarsely.
Melt butter in top of double boiler over hot water.
Add rest of ingredients.
Add clam juice.
When hot, add clams and cook slowly 15 minutes.
If not to be used immediately, refrigerate or freeze.
Bring milk to a scald and add to clams.
Add seasoning to milk mixture and heat thoroughly. Serves 5.

title: hot chicken or turkey salad
directions: Cube 4 slices bread into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine meat, celery, onions, salad dressing and salt.
Spread over bread. Cube 4 more slices of bread and put on top of salad mixture.
Beat eggs and milk.
Pour over other ingredients in casserole and let stand overnight, covered, in refrigerator.
Spread undiluted soup evenly over casserole and bake 1 hour.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake 15 minutes more.
Serves 8.

title: hobo dinners
directions: Make ground beef into 6 (1/2-inch) patties.
Lay each on an 18 x 12-inch square of heavy duty foil.
Salt and pepper meat to taste.
Then sprinkle each with 2 teaspoons of the brown gravy mix. Put 1/3 cup of frozen vegetables on each patty and then 7 or 8 Tater Tots.
Wrap each in foil and bake in a 400° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: saucy pork chops
directions: Brown chops in grease and season with salt and pepper.
Drain off fat.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chops. Cover and bake at 350° for 59 to 60 minutes.

title: cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Coat 8 x 8-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray. Combine cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in bowl. Add egg, milk and butter. Stir until all ingredients are moistened. Pour into pan. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool in pan on wire rack.

title: rice and vegetable stuffing
directions: In saucepan, cook carrot, onion and parsley in butter for 10 minutes, stirring frequently. Add broth, salt and pepper. Cook, covered, over low heat until rice is done, about 20 minutes. Use to stuff 2 (3 to 4 pound) roasting chickens (or one 6 to 7 pound capon) or bake, covered, in 1 1/2-quart casserole at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 5 cups.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Melt butter and stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil without stirring for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in soda and vanilla. Gradually pour over popcorn and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into baking pans.
Bake in a 250° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Break apart.

title: yellow frosted punch
directions: Freeze pineapple juice in can.
Remove from freezer about 2 hours before serving and store in refrigerator.
Have all juices reconstituted and chilled.
Remove pineapple juice from can; chop with large knife.
Place in punch bowl.
Add juices.
Chop sherbet into small pieces.
Pour in chilled ginger ale.
Yields 40 to 48 servings.

title: spicy ham balls
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and form into balls (about 1 tablespoon per ball).
Place balls in oblong sprayed dish.
Mix remaining ingredients; stir until sugar dissolves.
Pour over ham balls.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour; baste often.
Serves 40.

title: broccoli pudding
directions: In baking dish, place frozen broccoli, then stuffing mix and margarine.
Add corn to eggs and pour over broccoli and stuffing. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: In large bowl mix flour, sugar and salt. Melt oleo, cocoa and water; bring to a boil.
Pour melted mixture over flour (it will be thin).
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Bake in 11 x 17-inch sheet pan 20 minutes at 400°.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat the dry cake mix, buttermilk, egg whites and egg on low speed until moistened. Beat on high for 2 minutes. Transfer to 13 x 9 inch baking pan coated with nonstick cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 25 - 30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool on wire rack.

title: lemon crisps
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring mixture well.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place about 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheets.

title: cheesy wiener wheels
directions: Cut a slice of cheese into fourths.
Place cheese on a round cracker.
Cut wiener into circles.
Place wiener circle on cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: butterhorn rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and 2 tablespoons of sugar in warm tap water. Cream the butter with well beaten eggs.
Add yeast mixture, 1/2 cup of flour, salt and remaining 1/2 cup of sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Add rest of flour and mix by spoon.
Place in greased bowl and cover.
Set in refrigerator overnight.

title: russian fluff
directions: Brown onion and hamburger; drain grease.
Add rest of ingredients and put in baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: rio grande pork roast
directions: Combine the salt, garlic salt and chili powder. Rub on roast. In small saucepan, combine the jelly, catsup, vinegar and chili powder. Bring to a
boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 2 minutes. Brush roast with glaze.
Baste often with remaining glaze.
Bake in a 350° oven. Add water to pan drippings for a delicious gravy.

title: fudge krispies
directions: Melt chips, margarine and syrup.
Stir in vanilla and sugar. Add Rice Krispies and pour in a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Store in refrigerator.

title: cabbage relish
directions: Remove seeds and veins from bell pepper.
Chop cabbage; cut up bell pepper and onions, set aside.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple.
Save 1 cup juice from each and cook with pudding until it bubbles and gets clear.
Drain cherries and rinse with water.
Stir drained fruit and pudding together. When ready to serve, add 4 or 5 bananas.

title: corn pudding
directions: Grease casserole. Mix all ingredients and bake at 375° until firm, about an hour.

title: mexican salsa(mild)
directions: Dip tomatoes in boiling water for 30 to 60 seconds; dip in cold water and slip off skins.
Core, squeeze out seed cavities and chop tomatoes.
In a 6-quart saucepot, combine tomatoes and remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.

Reduce heat and simmer 30 to 60 minutes or to desired thickness, stirring occasionally. (Can thicken with cornstarch and cold water, if desired.) Immediately fill hot pint jars with mixture, leaving 1/2 inch headspace.
Wipe jar tops and threads clean.
Place hot lids on jars and screw bands on firmly.
Process in boiling water canner for 15 minutes.
Makes 5 pints.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender. Drain and rinse in hot water. Drain again. Mix noodles, tuna and soup together. Place in a casserole dish. Top with cheese and potato chips. Bake at 350° until bubbly. Remove from oven and serve.

title: taco dip
directions: Mash avocados with lemon juice, salt and pepper. Combine mayonnaise, sour cream and taco seasoning.
Spread beans on bottom of a large casserole dish, top with avocado mixture.
Spread on sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle on chopped onions, tomatoes and olives.
Cover with cheese. Serve with Tostitos.

title: holiday salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and milk.
Chill for one hour.
Add cherry pie filling, coconut, marshmallows, pineapple and nuts.
Mix well and chill overnight.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: squash casserole
directions: Stew squash until tender; drain.
Put margarine in while warm.
Add stuffing mix.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350° in greased 2-quart dish.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Combine hamburger, cheese and tomatoes in 2-quart saucepan.
Melt slowly over low heat; stirring occasionally.
Serve hot with chips.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixer bowl, mix ingredients. Beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Spoon batter into a well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake 40 to 45 minutes until cake tests for doneness. Cool on wire rack.
Remove from pan. Sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: steak au poivre
directions: Place peppercorns in plastic bag; crush with rolling pin. Press crushed peppercorns into meat on both sides.
Allow steaks to stand 1/2 hour to absorb flavor.
Keep refrigerated.
Heat oil and butter in pan.
Add steaks; cook quickly on both sides to seal in juices.
Continue cooking until done to your preference. Remove steaks to platter.
Stir wine in same pan.
Bring to boil, scraping pan.
Reduce wine to 1/4 cup; stir in cream.
Heat, but do not boil.
Pour over steaks.
Serves 4.

title: teriyaki beef
directions: Marinate meat in sauce for at least 4 hours.
Make sure meat is completely covered by sauce or turn periodically to make sure all parts of meat are absorbing sauce.
Best results when meat is cooked on outdoor grill.

title: fast and easy pancakes
directions: Place milk, sugar, eggs, oil and vanilla in the blender.
Add flour and baking powder.
Blend until smooth.
Heat a lightly oiled griddle or frying pan over medium-high heat.
Pour or scoop the batter onto the griddle, using approximately 1/4 cup for each pancake.
Brown on both sides and serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: zeppoles
directions: Mix first four ingredients, then add enough milk to make a thick batter.
Heat oil in deep fryer to approximately 350°.
Fry portions of batter a few at a time.
Do not crowd.
Drain on paper.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix together and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400°.

title: cranberry-orange bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour bottoms of 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Combine first 6 ingredients.
Mix well and set aside. Beat orange juice and orange peel and eggs until well mixed.
Add to dry ingredients. Mix just until moistened.
Fold in cranberries and nuts and pour into prepared pan.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes or until a wooden pick comes out of center clean.
Cool 10 minutes, then remove from pan.
Cool thoroughly before cutting.
Makes 12 servings.

title: cucumber pickle
directions: Put enough salt in water to float an egg. Put whole cucumbers in water. Soak in salt brine 8 to 10 days. Then cut cucumbers in slices. Soak in 1 teaspoon alum to 1 gallon water. Cover pickles in water for 48 hours. Drain. Fill pan 1/2 full with water. Add 1 tablespoon alum and 1 tablespoon turmeric. Boil 30 minutes. Take out of water. Put in vinegar, water and sugar. Add pickling spices. Boil 30 minutes. Pack in jars.

title: overnight oatmeal muffins
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine flours, oat bran, rolled oats, brown sugar, baking powder, soda, cinnamon, salt, buttermilk, safflower oil, egg and apricots. Stir in raisins. Cover and refrigerate overnight, or bake at once. Fill paper-lined muffin cups 3/4 full with batter. Bake at 400° 20-25 minutes, or until toothpick inserted into center comes out dry. Remove muffins from tins and cool on wire racks. Makes 14 servings.

title: chocolate covered cherry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease and lightly flour a 9x13x2 inch baking pan. In large bowl, cream together the butter and sugar.
Add the egg yolks one at a time, beating well after each addition. Combine

the flour and baking powder in a small bowl. Stir to mix. Add to the creamed mixture alternately with the milk, starting and ending with the flour mixture. Stir in the walnuts and cherries. Beat the egg whites until stiff. Fold into the batter. Pour into prepared pan and bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean when inserted into center of layer. While cake bakes, make the frosting.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and shape into balls.
Mix soup, water and sugar and pour over meatballs.
Cook 30 to 35 minutes.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple and add jello until dissolved, then cool.
Add the buttermilk, Cool Whip and nuts. Sprinkle with coconut. Chill overnight.

title: fruit dessert
directions: Heat sugar, cornstarch, yolks and milk in saucepan to a boil. Remove and add vanilla.
Layer ingredients, starting with ladyfingers.
Garnish with Cool Whip and kiwi fruit.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Add crushed crackers and margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: new orleans casserole
directions: Butter casserole and line with crumbs.
Alternate layers of asparagus, chicken, cheese and crumbs.
Prepare sauce by heating together milk, Lea & Perrins and mushroom soup.
Pour sauce over casserole and top with cheese and crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Cook 45 minutes at 350°.

title: beef brisket
directions: Line a pan with several layers of foil.
Trim excess fat from brisket.
Sprinkle brisket with meat tenderizer, salt and pepper; pierce meat evenly.

title: chicken tetrazzini(low-fat)
directions: Cut chicken into bite-size pieces, then cook with 1 cup water, onion, bay leaf, celery, salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Saute all vegetables and garlic in low-fat margarine until soft.
Add chicken, cream, stock and lemon juice.
Season with salt and pepper; cook slowly over low heat until heated through.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions, salt, green and red pepper and let stand for two hours.
Drain in colander.
Combine and mix well vinegar, sugar and celery seed.
Pour over cucumbers and let stand in refrigerator for 4 days.
Pack in jars and keep refrigerated.

title: cranberry meatballs
directions: Mix beef, corn flake crumbs, parsley, eggs, soy sauce, pepper, catsup, onion and garlic powder.
Shape into meatballs and place in baking dish.
Mix together remaining ingredients and pour over meatballs.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have cheese at room temperature.
Chop dried beef.
Blend all ingredients together; shape into ball and serve with crackers.

title: indian beans
directions: Cook the meat separate and brown real good. Mix cooked meat, barbecue sauce, both cans of beans and the onion (chopped) in a cooking pot. Bring to a boil. Turn down heat and simmer for 30 minutes, then get ready to enjoy heaven on earth. Makes about 6 normal servings. If I'm eating it, two servings.

title: jewelry dough
directions: Mix over heat until it gets to a mashed potato consistency, then knead.

Store in a plastic bag in the refrigerator overnight or use right away and watch it harden in a few hours. Great dough to use for making hand print plaques, candle holders or cookie cutter Christmas tree decorations.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, flour and salt.
Add egg yolks and milk. Cook on stove until thick, stirring constantly to keep from sticking.
Take off of stove and add butter and vanilla.
Put in baked pie shell and top with meringue.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 12-inch pan.
Pour in contents of pie filling and spread.
Sprinkle cake mix on top of filling.
Top with melted butter.
Sprinkle on nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool and serve with whipped topping.

title: cheese puffs *
directions: Mix together cheese, onion, garlic, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Let sit 1/2 hour.
Fold in egg whites.
Mold on crackers and broil.
Serve warm.

title: pat's chili
directions: Brown hamburger, chili seasoning and chili powder together. Add ketchup and water and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: banana slush punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar, water and pineapple juice.
Puree bananas in blender and add to Kool-Aid mixture.
Freeze in large container for 2 days or until ready to use.
Thaw for 3 to 4 hours; stir to slush.

title: "fried" potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes well, leaving skin on; cut lengthwise into strips.
Combine oil and seasonings in a plastic bag.
Add potatoes, a few at a time and shake well to coat.
Spread strips on two cookie sheets in a single layer.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown and tender.
Makes 6 servings. Contains 175 calories per serving and 24 milligrams sodium per serving.

title: chicken broccoli
directions: Cook and bone chicken.
Cook broccoli; layer in pan.
Combine other ingredients; mix.
Pour over chicken and broccoli; pat with butter.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: holiday sausage
directions: Brown sausage in electric frypan.
Add strips of green pepper and simmer 6 hours.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, sweetener and peanut butter and blend well.
Combine egg, milk and vanilla.
Add to creamed mixture. Sift flour, salt and baking powder; add to creamed mixture.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet and flatten with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yield:
2 dozen cookies. Carbohydrate 5.6 g, protein 2.2 g, fat 3.9 g, calories per cookie 54.
Three cookies = 1/4 bread exchange, 1 fat, 1/4 lean meat exchange

title: applesauce pecan pie
directions: Combine
butter,
sugar
and cinnamon.	Add applesauce, syrup, pecans and eggs.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Reduce
heat
to 325° and bake for 25 to 30 additional minutes.
Delicious!

title: pumpkin cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese and 1 tablespoon milk in bowl; add Cool Whip and mix.
Pour in pie crust.
Pour 1 cup milk in bowl; add pudding.
Beat with wire whisk 1 minute (mixture will be thick). Stir in pumpkin and spices.
Mix until well blended.
Spread on top of cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: brownies
directions: Mix in a pan and bring to a boil 1 cup water, 1 cube margarine, 3 1/2 tablespoons cocoa and 1/2 cup shortening.

Mix together in a large bowl flour and sugar; add to first mixture. Then mix in a small bowl the eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla. Add to mixture and bake in a large 12 x 15-inch sheet pan at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail salad
directions: Drain one can of fruit cocktail.
Add one small package of lemon jello to juice and boil; cool.
Prepare and add one package of Dream Whip or Cool Whip to jello.
Mix well.
Add fruit cocktail, marshmallows, cherries (broken in pieces) and one third cup of mayonnaise.
Freeze.

title: "fidel" spanish noodles
directions: You will need 12 or 10-inch heavy skillet.

title: easy onion flatbread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly spray 2 large baking sheets with no-stick cooking spray.
Prepare hot roll mix according to directions, stirring in wheat germ, basil, oregano and garlic with water, egg and margarine.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Melt butter; add rhubarb and sugar.
Cook slowly until rhubarb is tender.
Combine 1/4 cup sugar, cornstarch, egg yolks, Pet milk and salt.
Add to rhubarb and cook until thickened. Cool and pour into baked pie shell.

title: buckeyes
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients and form into balls.
Melt chocolate and paraffin in microwave or stove top.
Use toothpicks to cover 3/4 of peanut butter balls with chocolate. Set on waxed paper.

title: original chex party mix
directions: Combine margarine, Worcestershire sauce and seasoned salt; mix well.
Pour cereals, nuts and pretzels into large zipper bag. Pour margarine mixture over cereal mixture inside bag.
Seal top of bag securely.
Shake bag until all pieces are evenly coated. Pour contents of bag into large microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes, stirring thoroughly every 2 minutes. While stirring, make sure to scrape sides and bottom of bowl. Spread on absorbent paper to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: frosted pumpkin bars
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Beat oil, eggs, pumpkin and nuts well and then add to first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sparkling punch bowl
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Combine ginger ale and ice cubes to make 8 cups.
Add to gelatin, stirring until slightly thickened.
Remove any unmelted ice.
Measure 4 cups of gelatin and set aside.
Fold cut up fruit and pineapple chunks into remaining gelatin. Pour into large punch bowl.
Chill until set, but not firm.
Whip reserved gelatin until thick and fluffy and double in size.
Pour over top of gelatin and chill until firm.

title: rich green rice
directions: Saute celery and onion in margarine.
Mix all other ingredients in an 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 10-inch baking dish.
Add sauteed celery and onion.
Cover and bake 30 minutes at 350°. Serves 4.

title: crab or lobster newburg
directions: Melt butter in large skillet; blend in flour and seasonings. Gradually add cream and egg yolks, sherry and crab or lobster. Bake at 350° in individual casseroles until custard consistency. Serve hot.

title: burritos
directions: To brown ground beef, add the burrito seasoning mix and water as called for on package; stir in well, then add the salsa and mix in also.
Simmer (on low) for 15 minutes, then add cooked, drained potatoes.
Simmer 5 more minutes.
Next, place about 3 to 4 tablespoons of meat mixture onto a tortilla, sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of cheese, then tightly roll tortilla up and secure with toothpick.
Do all the tortillas, then on a flat skillet place 3 or 4 tortillas and pat butter onto them on both sides and brown evenly.
Finish all tortillas and take toothpicks out. Serve with sour cream.
These reheat well also.

title: betty thomas's 60-minute parker house rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Combine milk, sugar, salt and half of butter in saucepan.
Heat to lukewarm.
Add yeast and flour. Cover.
Put in a warm place for 15 minutes.
Turn onto a floured board.
Roll into 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with a large cutter. Apply butter.
Fold over.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: In small bowl, combine tomato sauce, brown sugar and mustard. Set aside.

title: "egg" salad sandwich spread
directions: Spray an 8-inch non-stick skillet with vegetable spray.
Pour eggs into skillet.
Cover tightly and cook over very low heat until just firm to touch.
Remove from skillet and cut into small pieces.
Add remaining ingredients and toss well.
Chill before serving.
Makes filling for 4 sandwiches.
Contains 110 calories and 5 gms. fat per 1/2 cup serving.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into large casserole dish. Cook until brown at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Check often.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mash 5 bananas and add ingredients listed.
Mix and freeze in tray or carton.
Serves about 15.

title: marble fudge brownies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy. Beat in eggs until blended. Mix in vanilla. Stir together flour, baking powder and salt. Then stir into creamed mixture. Spoon 1/2 batter into another bowl. Dissolve coffee crystals in water. Stir coffee and melted unsweetened chocolate into remaining batter. Drop chocolate mixture from tablespoon, checkerboard fashion, into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Fill in spaces with light batter. Swirl with spatula to marble; don't over-mix. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Immediately sprinkle light chocolate pieces over top. Let stand 2 to 3 minutes to melt. Spread chocolate evenly over brownies. Sprinkle with almonds. Cool. Cut into squares.

title: crock-pot peanut clusters
directions: Mix and melt white almond bark, chocolate chips and square of baking chocolate in crock-pot on high. Turn off.
Add nuts. Drop onto waxed paper with teaspoon. Cool.

title: easy apple pie
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake one hour at 350°.
Makes two pies.
These freeze well.

title: beef and potato skillet
directions: In a skillet, brown ground beef and onion until tender (drain off grease).
Mix soup and water together.
Pour into ground beef mixture and add sliced potatoes.
Mix all together and heat about 5 minutes, stirring often.

title: stir-fried rice
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons oil in pan.
Pour in eggs and stir-fry egg until in tiny pieces.
Remove from pan.
Heat 3 tablespoons oil. Stir-fry shrimp and meat; add green peas.
Fry 1 minute and remove.
Heat 3 tablespoons oil; fry onion and cooked rice.
Add salt.
Reduce heat.
Heat thoroughly.
Add egg and meat mixtures. Combine well and serve.

title: 1 minute frosting
directions: Put all ingredients together and boil 1 minute, stirring constantly. Take off heat and beat until right consistency to spread.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Add milk and lemon juice to cream cheese.
Blend well.
Add everything else, except shrimp.
Fold in shrimp.
Chill 6 hours or overnight.
Serve on crackers, celery or Melba rounds.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Melt the butter.
Add the onion and green pepper and fry 3 minutes.
Add the tomatoes, water, salt, pepper, sugar and okra. Slice thin.
Heat slowly to boiling point.
Add the shrimp and cook slowly for 10 minutes.
Serve in deep bowls with the oyster crackers.

title: chicken rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients except croutons.
Fill crescent rolls with mixture.
Dip in melted butter.
Put in casserole dish, top with croutons.
Bake at 375 degrees or until done.

title: rainbow jello
directions: Make Jello in the order given.
Use a 9 x 13-inch glass pan and make sure a layer is well set before adding a new layer.
Layers 1, 3, 5 and 7; mix Jell-O with 3/4 cup hot water and 3/4 cup cold water.
Layers 2, 4 and 6; mix Jell-O with 1/2 cup hot water, 1/2 cup cold water and 1/3 can sweetened condensed milk.

title: applesauce-raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add frozen raspberries and stir until thawed.
Stir in applesauce.
Pour into 10 x 6 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.
Chill until set.
Combine sour cream and marshmallows.
Spread atop jello.
Chill overnight before serving.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: In greased 8-inch baking dish, arrange uncooked noodles, cheese, spinach and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Uncooked noodles will be done.

title: california dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add Wish-Bone Italian dressing to moisten or to taste.
Prepare a day ahead.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Serve at room temperature with Fritos chips.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Heat oven to 325. Mix coconut, sugar, flour, and salt in a large mixing bowl. Stir in beaten egg whites and vanilla until well blended. Drop by spoonful onto greased cookie sheets. Bake 20 minutes or until edges of cookies are golden brown. Remove from cookie sheets. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: chopped apple cake
directions: Stir well and bake in 8 x 12-inch pan at 325° for 1 hour. This makes a moist cake and does not have to be frosted.
Good with Cool Whip.

title: baked cheese grits casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bring the water to a boil in a large saucepan; stir in the grits and continue to stir until they are completely mixed.
Cook, stirring, until thickened.
Whisk the eggs slightly, then stir a small amount of grits into the eggs to warm them.
Beat egg mixture into the grits off the heat.
Add the salt, garlic, paprika, Tabasco, cheese and butter, mixing well.
Pour the grits mixture into the buttered casserole.
Bake for 25 to 45 minutes, depending on the depth of the dish.
May be cooked in advance and reheated.
Freezes well.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cheesy scalloped potatoes
directions: For Sauce:
In a small saucepan, stir together milk, flour, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick and bubbly.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix crushed crackers with cheese.
Layer 1/2 of this mixture in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place asparagus pieces on top of crackers and cheese.
Place sliced eggs over asparagus and pour soup over all.
Layer remaining cracker mixture on top of soup. Chill for 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Mix sage and onion croutons, margarine and water.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with 1/2 of mixture.
Mix chicken, onion, celery, mayo and salt and place over croutons.
Place rest of croutons on chicken.
Beat eggs and milk.
Pour over croutons.
You can drizzle 1/4 cup butter over.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Before baking, add mushroom or chicken soup on top. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: barbecue beef loaf
directions: Pour milk over bread crumbs.
Add ground beef, salt, pepper, carrot, onion and beaten eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
Pack into 5 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Mix together catsup, brown sugar and mustard and spread on loaf.
Bake at 300° for about 1 1/2 hours or until brown and done.
Makes 8 servings.

title: squash casserole or souffle
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender, drain and add salt, pepper and sugar.
Combine cheese, crumbs, eggs, milk and butter with squash, saving some crumbs and cheese for the top.
Bake in a buttered casserole at 275° for 45 minutes.

title: company casserole
directions: Cook meat until it has lost its color.
Add salt, pepper and tomato sauce.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Alternate layer of noodle mixture and meat in 2-quart casserole dish. Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes until browned on top.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes, cut into chunks, boil until tender and let cool.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Cut into small chunks.
Add pickle juice, chopped pickles, eggs, cut eggs into small chunks.
Add onion, mayonnaise and mustard.

title: crumb mix
directions: Mix well.
Put 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon on top of fruit and then
top
with
crumb mix.
Bake at 350° for
to
45 minutes. For on top of pies and cobblers.

title: apple crumble
directions: Peel, core and cut into eighths the large cooking apples. Mix in a 1-quart glass baking dish with sugar, juice of lemon and cinnamon.

title: seafoam(candy)
directions: Boil sugar, corn syrup and water together until it forms a hard ball when dropped in water.

title: a christian cake
directions: Cut Nahum 3:12 into small pieces.
Coat this and 1 Samuel 30:12 in 1/2 cup 1 Kings 4:22.
Add Numbers 17:8.
Cream together Judges 5:25 and Jeremiah 6:20.
Add Isaiah 10:14, one at a time, beating well after each one.

title: potato soup(low-fat)
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan combine potatoes, water, onion, celery and chicken bouillon granules.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat. Cover and cook 20 minutes.
Mash potatoes slightly.
Do not drain.

title: glazed apple cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and milk.
Mix together flour and spices and add to creamed mixture; stir in nuts, apples and raisins.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Blend mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar and catsup. Fold in relish and egg. Cover and chill.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook chicken breasts.
Save broth.
Cut up chicken in small pieces.
Mix stuffing mix according to directions.
Add mayonnaise to cut-up chicken.
Add this to stuffing mix.
Cook shells, stuff with stuffing mix.
Put in glass baking dishes.
Add chicken broth to chicken soup.
Pour over shells and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 40.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat together egg and sugar.
Beat in milk and vanilla.
Serve cold sprinkled lightly with nutmeg.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise and sour cream together.
Squeeze all water out of thawed spinach using hands.
Mix spinach and remaining ingredients together with mayonnaise and sour cream.
Cover and chill at least 4 hours (overnight is better).

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Soak oats in water, then add oleo and sugar.
Pour in tube pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes, then take out of oven and let cool.

title: cracker barrel hash brown potato casserole
directions: Butter sides of covered casserole.
Add a little butter on top of all the listed ingredients.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes. Remove cover and let brown on top a few minutes.

title: punch
directions: Bring water and sugar to a boil.
Simmer 3 minutes.
Add gelatin and stir well.
Add lemon juice, orange juice and water and pineapple juice.
Mix together and freeze.
Set out 2 hours before serving.
Just before serving, pour 2 bottles ginger ale over this.

title: banana split cake
directions: First layer, Mix together the first 3 ingredients and press into a 9 x 13 pan, freeze for 10-15 minutes.

title: marinated dill carrots
directions: Combine ingredients and marinate several hours or overnight.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix in large bowl Bran Buds and crushed Shredded Wheat. Pour boiling water over
cereal.
Let
cool.
Cream
sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and buttermilk.
Slowly mix into cereal. Add flour and baking
soda.
Mix
only
until
blended.
Don't overmix.
Bake at 400° for
minutes.
Batter can be frozen or kept in the refrigerator.
Do
not stir batter again.
Just spoon into muffin papers.

title: slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and carrots.
Chop onion.
In large bowl, place 2-inches of cabbage, carrots and onion.
Add remaining cabbage and sprinkle with sugar.

title: russian bread dip
directions: *Other whole rounds of bread can also be used in place of the rye bread, such as pumpernickel.

title: upside-down cheesecake
directions: Prepare lemon cake mix as directed.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch oblong glass or cake pan.
Cream together other ingredients.
Beat well.
Pour over unbaked cake mix.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Cake will rise to top, cheese mix goes to the bottom.

title: quick chocolate fudge nut cake
directions: Sift
together flour and sugar.
Bring water, margarine and cocoa to
boil.
Pour over flour and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat	until
smooth
and
bake
in
greased
and floured 9 x 12-inch pan in preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes. Pour hot icing over warm cake.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter; stir in flour and mix well.
Add milk, diced onion, salt and cheese.
Heat until slightly thickened.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Melt shortening and brown meat.
Stir in flour, salt, thyme and pepper, scraping well.
Place all in 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour in 1 can of broth.
Bake 2 hours in 325° oven.
Add mushrooms, onions, 1 can broth and 1/2 cup of wine.
Bake 1 1/2 hours more until tender.
Serves 8.

title: texas pecan cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and lemon extract. Add flour to raisins and nuts.
Add to mixture.
Bake 2 hours at 275° in a tube pan or a 10 x 14-inch loaf pan.
Line pan with paper.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all in order given; mix well.
Spray 1 loaf pan with Pam. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy corned beef and cabbage
directions: Fry bacon strips until done in heavy skillet.
Remove bacon; put 1 head chopped cabbage in bacon drippings.
Add small amount of water; cover and steam until cabbage is tender.
Make a well in the middle of the steamed cabbage.
Once liquid is cooked out, add can of corned beef and let it heat through.
Serve with cornbread.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix oil and sugar; add eggs, flour, soda, salt and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Stir in apples, coconut and nuts.
(Batter may seem stiff.)
Place in greased tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy lemon cheese cake
directions: Stir cream cheese until very soft.
Gradually blend in 1/2 cup milk until smooth and creamy.
Add remaining milk and the pudding mix.
Beat slowly with eggbeater for 1 minute.
(Do not overbeat.) Pour into cool graham cracker crust.

title: granny's cookies
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add and blend well.
Add vanilla, oatmeal, chips and nuts.
Mix well. I cover my cookie sheets in foil, then drop small pinches of dough 2 inches apart and bake at 350° until light brown.
Makes lots of cookies.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Crumble ground beef in 2-quart casserole; add green pepper. Mix in soup mix, chili powder, tomato sauce, tomato paste, olives and water.
Heat through.
Place 2 tortillas in 12 x 7-inch baking dish.
Top with 1/2 meat mixture and half of both cheeses. Repeat.
Microwave 5 minutes; rotate and microwave another 5 minutes until cheese melts.
Top with shredded lettuce, sour cream and tomato.

title: laundry mat cake
directions: Cream together Crisco and margarine.
Add sugar and beat.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat after adding each one.
Sfit flour and add alternately with milk until the 3 cups of flour are blended. Add vanilla.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven in 8 x 12 x 2-inch pan or tube pan.

title: pinanna cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, soda and cinnamon in a large mixing bowl.
Add oil and eggs.
Stir until moistened; do not beat.
Stir in bananas, pineapple, vanilla and pecans.
Bake at 350° until done, about 1 hour.
Refrigerate left over cake.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.
Garnish with pecan halves.

title: george's heart-healthy peach ice cream
directions: Scald evaporated skim milk.
Mix together sugar, egg substitute, Jell-O and salt with electric mixer, beating 5 minutes on medium to high speed.
Add hot milk gradually to egg substitute and sugar mixture.
Pour into pan and heat mixture until it coats spoon.
Add vanilla.
Add peaches that have been blended.
Pour mixture into 1 gallon ice cream freezer container.
Add skim or nonfat milk until container is 3/4 full and freeze according to freezer directions.
Freeze leftover in individual paper cups for easy serving.

title: sausage pie
directions: Stir together.
Put in casserole dish.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients and then bake in a casserole dish for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: snook-fish deep fry batter
directions: In separate bowl, beat 1 egg white until it is stiff.
Mix first 5 ingredients until smooth.
Fold in egg white.
Fold in olive oil.
Dip paper towel-dried chunks of fish in batter and drop into hot oil.
Cook until brown.
(Try to avoid dropping on top of each other.
This will make the pieces stick together when cooked.)

title: happy times punch
directions: Combine frozen juices and water.
Place ice cream and sherbet in the bottom of the bowl, break into small pieces and add juices.
Stir all together until frozen ingredients are slightly melted.

title: strawberry-rhubarb jam
directions: Stir sugar in rhubarb and let stand until juicy (about 1 hour).
Cook until tender; add jello.
Stir; pour in jars and cover.
Store in freezer when cool.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan (greased/floured) at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: carrot raisin muffins
directions: Combine carrots, nuts
and
raisins.
Set
aside.
Beat sugar with melted butter	until
light.
Add
eggs,
blending well. Stir in flour, baking powder, soda and salt, just until flour is blended.
Fold in carrot mixture.
Grease muffin tins and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Place potatoes in casserole dish.
Mix the remaining ingredients except pork chops together.
Brown pork chops; put on top of potatoes and cover with mixture.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken 'n' rice
directions: Cut cooked chicken into tiny bite size pieces.
Heat cream of chicken soup in boiler; dilute with milk or water.
Add all ingredients together.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: sin cake
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Mix in nuts and flour to form crust in bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Pour 1/2 the batter in a 9 x 13-inch or larger pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool a little.
In meantime, melt caramels, butter and milk in a double boiler, stirring constantly.
Pour over baked cake half.
Sprinkle with 1 cup nuts and 1 cup chocolate chips.
Pour remaining cake mixture over this.
Sprinkle 1 cup chopped nuts over cake.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let stand before cutting.

title: carrot raisin salad
directions: Scrub carrots.
Scrape them and shred to make 2 cups.
Combine with raisins.
Mix yogurt, lemon juice and salt.
Pour over salad and mix thoroughly.

title: sandra's meat loaf
directions: Mix all
ingredients
with 1/3 cup of the tomato sauce. Spread in	a loaf pan and spread remaining sauce on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: tomato pie
directions: Precook-cook pastry shell.
Fill shell 3/4 full with tomatoes. Sprinkle with basil.
Mix together mayonnaise and cheeses.
Add salt and pepper.
Pile on top of tomatoes.

title: marie petersen's glorified rice
directions: Mix lemon jello according to directions, and cool till it starts to jell.

title: "mountain" fried pies
directions: Roll crust on a floured board.
Cut with a large cookie cutter.
Put 1 1/2 tablespoons sweetened, mashed, cooked fruit in each round.
Moisten edges with cold water and fold to make semi-circle; press edges together with a fork.
Fry in hot deep fat and drain well on paper towels when crispy brown.
Great on cold winter days or just anytime.

title: coke salad
directions: Boil cherries, sugar and water for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add jello.
Chill in refrigerator.
Add drained pineapple, nuts and Coke.
Let chill overnight.

title: african wedding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, sift and mix all ingredients.
Make a well in center of bowl.
Add unbeaten eggs, oil, vanilla, bananas and pineapple in the well in center of bowl. Stir, do not beat, until well blended.
Pour in greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: teriyaki glazed chicken(serving size:  6)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with foil.
Arrange chicken pieces, meaty-side down in pan.
In a small saucepan, combine other ingredients and bring to a boil over medium high heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute or until sugar dissolves.
Brush glaze over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, turn and brush with glaze.
Bake an additional 25 to 35 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender and juices run clear.

title: snappy asparagus dip
directions: Snap off and discard woody bases from asparagus.
If desired, scrape off scales.
Cook, covered, in a small amount of boiling water until very tender, about 15 minutes.
Drain; cool.
Place asparagus in blender container.
Cover; blend until smooth. Transfer to bowl.
Stir in sour cream, taco sauce, lime juice, salt, pepper and red pepper.
Chill, covered, up to 24 hours.

title: raisin spice bars
directions: In 2-quart saucepan combine sugar, raisins, water, margarine, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg and salt.
Bring to a boil and cook 3 minutes.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients, blend well.
Spread evenly in greased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Sprinkle topping evenly over top.
Press down lightly.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool and cut into squares.

title: o'henry bars
directions: Slightly boil sugar and Karo syrup.
Add peanut butter, peanuts and Rice Krispies.
Stir well.
Melt together chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
Spread on top of mix.
Let cool and serve.
Yummy!

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients together.
Beat eggs and oil together.
Combine with dry ingredients and fold in carrots.
Bake in 3 layers at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: bacon-lettuce-tomato salad
directions: Prepare Barbecue Salad Dressing.
Just prior to serving, tear lettuce into bite-size pieces (about 6 cups).
Break bacon into large pieces.
Cut each tomato into eighths.
Add bacon, tomatoes and chicken to lettuce; toss with dressing.
Garnish with egg slices.
Serves 4.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Mix together all ingredients except nuts.
Add nuts to mixture and toss lightly until well coated. Arrange in a single layer on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 45 minutes or until golden and crusty.
Remove from oven. Immediately remove nuts from cookie sheet.
Store in covered container.

title: fettucini picante
directions: Cook fettucini in saucepan according to package directions. In second saucepan over low heat, combine butter, picante sauce and cheese.
Cook and stir until butter melts.
Remove from heat; stir in sour cream and salt.
Add fettucini; toss.
Top with olives.

title: heavenly hamburger
directions: Brown ground beef; add salt and pepper, tomato sauce and finely minced garlic.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Whip cream cheese and sour cream until light and fluffy and add chopped onions.

title: hong kong pork chops
directions: Brown chops on both sides.
Arrange onion slices, mushrooms and water chestnuts on chops.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chops.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.
Serve with rice.

title: shelley's italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine ingredients in large pot.
Add the Hamburg after the Tomato Sauce and Tomato Paste.
Have the hamburg room temperature and crumble into the mixture with your fingers, stir with spoon until it is all through the sauce.
Cover and leave in 325 - 350 oven 3 - 6 hours.
If oven is 350, you'll need to stir every half hour.
Add water to maintain level.

title: orange pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 2 pie crusts and cool. Pour when cool (crusts) pie mix and chill.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Drain spinach; add egg yolks, 1 tablespoon butter, 1/2 cup milk and 3/4 of the cheese.
Mix together.
Beat egg whites.
Add to the mixture in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted thoroughly.
Melt remaining cheese with a little milk; pour on top of casserole.
When done, slice boiled egg and put on top.

title: pecan-oatmeal pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook on hot griddle.
Makes 12 to 16 pancakes.

title: janie's squares(snack)
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into jelly roll pan. Sprinkle 1 cup of nuts and a 6-ounce package of chocolate chips over the top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Make cornbread according to directions.
Saute onion and celery in 1/4 cup water.
Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix flour, salt, pepper, milk, onion, cheese and butter together.
Pour over sliced potatoes arranged in a greased baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan melt butter.
Be sure butter is spread evenly in the pan.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter; pour Eagle Brand over crumbs.
Top with coconut, pecans and M&M's.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Cut up pieces of cooked chicken.
Mix all together.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: alligator sauce piquant
directions: Prepare a roux by heating cooking oil and then adding flour; stir over medium heat until mixture turns a dark brown.
Mix and brown all chopped vegetables and cook until onions are clear.
Add alligator meat and cook about 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients and cook for 2 more hours.
Add water to obtain desired consistency and serve over hot rice.
Yield:
1000 servings.

title: custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put the eggs, sugar, salt, nutmeg and vanilla together.
Make sure eggs are a fluffy lemon color before adding ingredients to it.
Add milk and mix together good.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake for about 30 minutes until a knife inserted in the custard comes out clean.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Beat eggs and sugar; add melted margarine.
Add milk, bread crumbs and pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cheese crust flank steak
directions: Combine wine, oil, vinegar, garlic and oregano in shallow nonaluminum pan.
Add steak, turning to coat.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 to 48 hours.
Combine cheese, mustard and Worcestershire in small bowl.
Drain steaks.
Grill 5 minutes on high heat.
Turn over and spread with cheese mixture.
Grill 5 more minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Flake tuna; add nuts and eggs.
Mix mayonnaise with lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, salt and pepper.
Add to tuna and put into a 9-inch square pan.
Put buttered bread crumbs on top and bake about 20 minutes, until golden brown, in a 400° oven.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pasta pronto
directions: Place tomatoes, oil and garlic in frying pan.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Heat on medium heat for 5 minutes.
Add basil and white wine to pan; heat 3 more minutes.
Cook pasta according to directions and drain well.
Stir sauce in pan and pour over penne.
Enjoy!

title: hawaiian nut sandwiches
directions: Blend milk and cheese together.
Add pineapple and nuts. Blend well and spread between thin slices of buttered orange or raisin bread.

title: spinach and tomatoes
directions: Simmer ingredients together until tender.
Serve on pasta or plain.

title: okra and tomato soup
directions: Cook okra and tomatoes with salt, pepper and oil in a boiler. Have the corn meal mixed with hot water in a bowl ahead of time so that the meal will be dissolved.
When the okra and tomatoes get done, thicken it with the corn meal.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Store in refrigerator approximately 6 hours before serving.
Makes approximately 1 pint.

title: cranberry-raisin pie
directions: Chop cranberries and raisins (coarsely).
Mix in the remainder of ingredients and cook for ten minutes, stirring all the time. Cool.
Bake in a two-crust pie at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown.
Makes one 9-inch pie.
If you would like it fancy make a lattice work top.

title: stuffed puffs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In	saucepan, heat water and butter to rolling boil.
Stir in flour
and
stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball,
about 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Beat in eggs, all at
once,
until	smooth	and glossy. Drop dough by slightly rounded
teaspoonfuls
onto
greased or ungreased baking sheet.
Bake about
minutes until puffed, golden
brown and dry.
Puffs
can
be
stuffed
with
chicken salad, tuna, deviled ham, etc.

title: easy pancakes
directions: Blend egg and milk together.
Slowly beat in flour.
Fry over medium heat until golden brown.
If you like fruit in pancakes, add 1/2 cup.
Good with blueberries, strawberries or apples.

title: chow chow
directions: Chop green peppers, red peppers, onions and green tomatoes. Place all chopped peppers, onions and tomatoes in pot and mix. Pour boiling water over mixture to cover.
Let stand 5 minutes. Drain.
Pour boiling water over mixture again and let stand 10 minutes.
Drain and press all water out.
Mix liquid mixture preceding until boiling.
Add chopped ingredients to liquid and cook 30 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.
Makes 16 pints.

title: fruit pie
directions: Put fruit in Pyrex dish.
Place bread over fruit.
Melt margarine and sugar; add flour and egg.
Beat together and pour over slices of bread.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients together in a saucepan.
Heat on low heat for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: blueberry salad
directions: You will need a 9 x 13 pan.

title: crispy beef
directions: Thinly slice and cut the beef or steak into bite size pieces. Marinate for 5 to 6 minutes in a mixture of Sake, sesame oil and ginger juice. Mix together beaten egg, flour, cornstarch and baking powder. Coat meat with this mixture and deep fry in hot oil until crisp. Garnish with tomato wedges and parsley.

title: pizza
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water with salt.
Add flour and oil. Let set for 30 minutes before rolling out.
Bake until brown in 375° oven.

title: speedy salad
directions: Prepare pudding according to directions.
Fold in one cup whipped cream.
Fold fruit and marshmallows into the pudding mixture.
Chill thoroughly.

title: ultimate chocolate brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease rectangular pan (13 x 8 x 2-inches).
In medium bowl, combine cocoa and baking soda.
Blend in 1/3 cup melted butter.
Add boiling water; stir until mixture thickens.
Stir in sugar, eggs and remaining 1/3 cup melted butter; stir until smooth.
Add flour, vanilla and salt; blend completely.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour into pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool completely.
Cut into squares.
Makes about 3 dozen brownies.

title: captain's soup
directions: Brown meat and onion in large Dutch oven or stockpot.
Add salt and pepper, V-8, soups and water.
Bring to a boil and add mixed vegetables.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Quick and easy. Tastes like it cooked all day.

title: peach dessert
directions: Spread peaches and juice on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle cake mix over and dot with butter.
Cover with coconut and nuts.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes at 325°.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: champagne salad
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese.
Add fruit and nuts.
Mix well. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze overnight. Allow to thaw slightly (about 1/2 hour) before serving.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Cut chicken up into small pieces. Mix chicken soup, vegetables, parsley and poppy seed in baking dish. Place pie shell on top and bake at 400° until pie shell is done.

title: mangino's lasagna
directions: Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan the uncooked noodles, a spreading of sauce and meat mixture, and 1/2 package of Mozzarella cheese. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Repeat this layering until the pan is full.
(Crisscross the noodles and add a little water to each layer so the noodles will cook evenly.)
Cover with foil and cook at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Freezes well.

title: overnight chix dish
directions: Mix together and put into covered, greased casserole dish and refrigerate overnight. Take out 1 hour before baking.
Crush potato chops on top. Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: zucchini bread in pint jars
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Beat eggs, zucchini and water. Sift together dry ingredients and add to zucchini; stir well.
Add nuts.
Pour into wide mouth sterile jars.
Fill 1/2 full.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Remove jars from oven.
Wipe rims clean and cover with hot lids and bands.

title: chocolate bread pudding
directions: Scald the cocoa and milk. Add the bread pieces. Take from stove and add the sugar, salt and eggs. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes. Top with whipped cream.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Peel eggs and cut in half lengthwise.
Take yolks out and mash with fork.
Add relish and mayonnaise to yolks.
Place this yolk mixture back into egg white halves.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix until smooth.
Fold in 1 (12 ounce) container Cool Whip.

title: marilyn's lasagna
directions: In a large deep pot, place olive oil, tomato paste and crumbled sausage. Brown mixture for about 6 minutes, stirring frequently. Add tomato sauce, onions, garlic, salt and pepper. Cover and simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Boil lasagna noodles. Use olive oil to grease bottom and sides of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place a layer of noodles on the bottom. Drop spoonfuls of gravy over them.
Sprinkle cheeses over this. Repeat layers until dish is full. Top with Parmesan cheese. Bake in a 350° oven for about 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: eagle brand lemon pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat egg yolks, stir in condensed milk, lemon juice and rind.
Mix well.
Pour into crust.
In small bowl, beat egg whites with cream of tartar until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff but not dry.
Spread meringue on top of pie, sealing carefully to edge of crust.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until meringue is golden brown.
Cool.
Chill before serving. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: chocolate morsel pie
